"My wife shouldn't find out.."

262
00:18:08,446 --> 00:18:09,696
"..or else they'll shoot me."

263
00:18:09,779 --> 00:18:11,738
Actually my daughter
Kajal is suffering..

264
00:18:11,821 --> 00:18:13,988
..from a split personality disorder.

265
00:18:14,154 --> 00:18:15,904
But there must be
a big reason behind that.

266
00:18:15,988 --> 00:18:17,988
The reason is inside, Doctor.

267
00:18:18,196 --> 00:18:19,279
That fool Arjun.

268
00:18:19,321 --> 00:18:21,029
She thought he's a hero.

269
00:18:21,320 --> 00:18:22,404
But after their marriage..

270
00:18:22,529 --> 00:18:24,363
..she found out that he's no hero,
but a big failure.

271
00:18:24,571 --> 00:18:26,404
That poor girl's
dreams were shattered.

272
00:18:26,779 --> 00:18:30,071
She kept her frustration in her heart.

273
00:18:30,154 --> 00:18:31,863
And because of that
she developed this ailment.

274
00:18:32,238 --> 00:18:33,696
And now the condition is, Doctor..

275
00:18:34,238 --> 00:18:40,571
..that Kajal has fits at
least once a day for ten minutes.

276
00:18:40,904 --> 00:18:42,404
And when she has the fits..

277
00:18:42,529 --> 00:18:44,863
..she wants to kill Arjun. - Oh no.

278
00:18:44,946 --> 00:18:46,071
Oh yes.

279
00:18:46,238 --> 00:18:48,071
I have to attend an important meeting.

280
00:18:48,238 --> 00:18:49,779
But my staff is right here.

281
00:18:52,321 --> 00:18:54,196
Excuse me, sir. Time for juice.

282
00:18:57,238 --> 00:18:58,320
Orange.

283
00:18:59,071 --> 00:19:02,238
No one in my family
has ever had orange juice.

284
00:19:03,779 --> 00:19:07,029
We only have pomegranate juice.
- Right.

285
00:19:07,196 --> 00:19:08,529
No problem, sir.

286
00:19:17,196 --> 00:19:18,321
Mummy.

287
00:19:26,238 --> 00:19:27,988
You want pomegranate juice?

288
00:19:31,363 --> 00:19:33,821
Has anyone in your family
ever seen a pomegranate?

289
00:19:35,529 --> 00:19:36,738
You're laughing.

290
00:19:36,821 --> 00:19:37,946
Am I joking?

291
00:19:38,029 --> 00:19:40,321
I am not laughing, Kajal.
I mean Kamini.

292
00:19:40,404 --> 00:19:43,071
I am feeling..
ticklish in the stomach.

293
00:19:43,154 --> 00:19:44,279
I see.

294
00:19:44,321 --> 00:19:46,779
I'll take care of your tickle.

295
00:19:46,946 --> 00:19:48,821
Or else, because of the
bullets in your stomach..

296
00:19:48,904 --> 00:19:50,821
..you'll keep laughing
in front of my Kajal..

297
00:19:50,904 --> 00:19:52,654
..and that poor girl will keep crying.

298
00:19:52,738 --> 00:19:54,029
Bullets? In my stomach.

299
00:19:54,113 --> 00:19:57,904
How could you survive after
being hit by so many bullets?

300
00:19:58,113 --> 00:19:59,238
If you had died..

301
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:01,320
..then at least Kajal would've
been free from your clutches.

302
00:20:01,363 --> 00:20:04,988
Why did you go to catch
Marcos alone? Tell me.

303
00:20:06,154 --> 00:20:08,363
You're a police officer,
but you got beaten up by criminals.

304
00:20:08,446 --> 00:20:09,613
Weren't you ashamed?

305
00:20:09,696 --> 00:20:12,529
I say.. I say, Kajal.

306
00:20:12,613 --> 00:20:14,404
Kajal, let's forget the past.

307
00:20:14,529 --> 00:20:17,279
I am dead. - Mummy. - Save me.

308
00:20:17,404 --> 00:20:19,321
Doctor. - Boss.
But you were bedridden.

309
00:20:29,821 --> 00:20:31,029
O my God!

310
00:20:32,154 --> 00:20:33,238
Sir barely survived.

311
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:36,321
"No problem."

312
00:20:37,320 --> 00:20:40,404
"No problem."

313
00:20:41,738 --> 00:20:43,529
My wife left me.

314
00:20:44,529 --> 00:20:46,029
I'm not scared of dying.

315
00:20:46,321 --> 00:20:48,321
I feel like jumping
out of this window.

316
00:20:58,320 --> 00:20:59,571
Save me.

317
00:21:00,571 --> 00:21:01,738
But you wanted to die.

318
00:21:01,821 --> 00:21:03,196
I have small children.

319
00:21:03,363 --> 00:21:04,904
I can't give them a mother's love..

320
00:21:04,988 --> 00:21:07,113
..but I can get them a new mother.

321
00:21:07,404 --> 00:21:09,738
Save me.
- Don't move. Someone save him.

322
00:21:09,821 --> 00:21:12,238
Boss. Doctor.
- Dad. - Look at him, what he's doing.

323
00:21:19,154 --> 00:21:20,571
How did this..

324
00:21:20,779 --> 00:21:21,863
What are you doing here?

325
00:21:22,529 --> 00:21:23,613
Actually,
Sister-in-law, there was a storm..

326
00:21:23,696 --> 00:21:24,821
..but luckily sir survived again.

327
00:21:26,696 --> 00:21:28,196
And what are you doing with this?

328
00:21:28,321 --> 00:21:30,529
Who brought this? Throw it away.

329
00:21:31,446 --> 00:21:33,279
Who is it?

330
00:21:34,154 --> 00:21:35,363
Oh, Lord.

331
00:21:35,904 --> 00:21:37,696
Someone threw a wreath on
me as soon as I entered this city.

332
00:21:38,404 --> 00:21:41,821
Seems like the entire
city knows those rascals.

333
00:21:44,404 --> 00:21:45,145
Come in.

334
00:21:48,154 --> 00:21:49,363
Stand at the back.

335
00:21:50,738 --> 00:21:51,821
Sir.

336
00:21:54,446 --> 00:21:56,446
Yash. - Get well soon, sir.

337
00:21:57,029 --> 00:21:58,154
Thank you, sir.

338
00:21:58,238 --> 00:22:00,529
Congratulations, you survived.
- Thank you.

339
00:22:04,238 --> 00:22:05,613
I don't want your flowers.

340
00:22:06,446 --> 00:22:09,154
Sir, you can accept his
flowers but not mine? - Shut up.

341
00:22:09,904 --> 00:22:11,571
Cheater, thief, blackmailer.

342
00:22:12,029 --> 00:22:13,821
You live with such a great man.

343
00:22:13,988 --> 00:22:16,114
Do some social work. Do something big.

344
00:22:16,154 --> 00:22:18,529
Be like him.
- I am better off the way I am.

345
00:22:18,571 --> 00:22:20,238
One day you'll die by my hands.

346
00:22:20,321 --> 00:22:22,696
Yash, ask him to get out..
of my sight.

347
00:22:22,904 --> 00:22:24,654
I said go. - Leave.

348
00:22:25,363 --> 00:22:28,404
Something happens every time..
I see him.

349
00:22:28,529 --> 00:22:29,863
Control yourself, sir.

350
00:22:30,029 --> 00:22:32,363
If you move,
your stitches will open up, sir.

351
00:22:32,654 --> 00:22:35,320
Control, sir. Control, sir. Control.

352
00:22:35,863 --> 00:22:37,613
Hi, Raj.

353
00:22:39,238 --> 00:22:40,446
Naughty boy.

354
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:42,863
Hi, darling.

355
00:22:43,613 --> 00:22:44,904
How are you?

356
00:22:46,779 --> 00:22:48,238
Who's he? - Rascal.

357
00:22:48,320 --> 00:22:50,154
Congratulations.

358
00:22:50,696 --> 00:22:51,904
Hi. - Hi.

359
00:22:52,529 --> 00:22:54,404
Raj, you.. here?

360
00:22:54,654 --> 00:22:56,154
You didn't send this
month's installment.

361
00:22:56,363 --> 00:22:58,821
I was slightly busy due
to my brother's engagement.

362
00:22:58,904 --> 00:23:01,613
That's why.. - I thought.. you forgot.

363
00:23:01,696 --> 00:23:03,571
You do remember your promise,
don't you, darling?

364
00:23:03,654 --> 00:23:06,738
Of course, you'll be my next actress.

365
00:23:06,821 --> 00:23:08,696
No. - Congrats! - Thank you.

366
00:23:09,238 --> 00:23:10,529
Why are you showing it again?

367
00:23:10,571 --> 00:23:11,988
I'll.. send it tomorrow.

368
00:23:12,071 --> 00:23:13,988
I get bored after
10 minutes in a party.

369
00:23:14,071 --> 00:23:15,279
Meet me right now.

370
00:23:16,363 --> 00:23:17,946
Sanjana. Sanjana.

371
00:23:18,029 --> 00:23:20,238
Sanjana. Sanjana.

372
00:23:20,320 --> 00:23:22,738
Where are you? - Sanjana. Sanjana.

373
00:23:23,196 --> 00:23:25,446
Sanjana. Sanjana.

374
00:23:26,029 --> 00:23:27,529
Where are you?

375
00:23:33,821 --> 00:23:35,904
Hi. - Hi. What's wrong?

376
00:23:35,988 --> 00:23:37,654
All your friends are searching
for you and you're hiding here.

377
00:23:37,738 --> 00:23:41,238
The girl who's getting
engaged is my best friend.

378
00:23:41,738 --> 00:23:44,071
I am not her enemy
that I'll go sit there.

379
00:23:44,863 --> 00:23:46,113
Enemy? I didn't understand?

380
00:23:46,196 --> 00:23:47,321
Oh, God.

381
00:23:47,988 --> 00:23:49,113
If I go and sit there..

382
00:23:49,196 --> 00:23:51,154
..then won't that boy
choose me over my friend.

383
00:23:51,238 --> 00:23:52,529
Your friend is quite
beautiful as well.

384
00:23:52,571 --> 00:23:54,529
I saw her. - Tell me something.

385
00:23:54,779 --> 00:23:57,320
What would you choose between
a television and plasma? - Plasma.

386
00:23:57,696 --> 00:23:59,946
And between an Indica and Ferrari.
- Ferrari.

387
00:24:00,029 --> 00:24:01,113
That is the difference.

388
00:24:01,696 --> 00:24:03,696
She's the television and I am plasma.

389
00:24:04,029 --> 00:24:05,654
She's Indica and I am Ferrari.

390
00:24:05,821 --> 00:24:07,113
I see.

391
00:24:07,404 --> 00:24:10,863
So you think you're the
most beautiful.. - "I think."

392
00:24:11,071 --> 00:24:12,154
What do you mean?

393
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:13,446
Just a minute

394
00:24:13,779 --> 00:24:14,904
Take a close look at me.

395
00:24:24,821 --> 00:24:27,571
You're beautiful,
but not as much as you think.

396
00:24:27,821 --> 00:24:29,571
I have a shack at Sunset beach.

397
00:24:29,654 --> 00:24:31,529
You can find me there
everyday. - What?

398
00:24:32,279 --> 00:24:33,988
You don't find me that beautiful..

399
00:24:34,071 --> 00:24:36,113
..so you won't come there either.

400
00:24:36,571 --> 00:24:37,696
We'll see.

401
00:24:43,029 --> 00:24:46,029
I think that girl's half crazy.
- Oh no, she's completely insane.

402
00:24:46,113 --> 00:24:47,404
But she's made me crazy as well.

403
00:24:49,529 --> 00:24:51,613
Who's creating a
commotion at midnight?

404
00:24:51,696 --> 00:24:53,320
Seems like a new tenant.

405
00:24:54,279 --> 00:24:55,613
He's not visible in the dark.

406
00:24:55,696 --> 00:24:56,863
Hello, my friend?

407
00:24:58,196 --> 00:25:00,738
What's this commotion?
- I am chopping wood.

408
00:25:01,071 --> 00:25:03,821
Is this the time to chop wood?
- It's cold now..

409
00:25:03,904 --> 00:25:05,613
..so should I chop
wood in the morning?

410
00:25:05,779 --> 00:25:07,321
During the day,
I was shivering with cold.

411
00:25:07,529 --> 00:25:09,446
What if I freeze to death at night?

412
00:25:09,654 --> 00:25:11,404
Will you take me to the crematorium?

413
00:25:12,113 --> 00:25:14,113
Won't you think about the neighbors?

414
00:25:14,196 --> 00:25:16,696
The neighbors didn't think about me.

415
00:25:16,779 --> 00:25:18,988
My heater broke down.
Did anyone lend me another one?

416
00:25:19,196 --> 00:25:21,571
These misers didn't even
give me a piece of wood.

417
00:25:21,904 --> 00:25:24,571
You give it. And I will
stop chopping wood. You give it.

418
00:25:24,654 --> 00:25:26,071
The heater in our house
is working perfectly.

419
00:25:26,154 --> 00:25:27,654
There's no wood in our house.

420
00:25:27,738 --> 00:25:30,821
There must be a chair, sofa, table..
dining table at home.

421
00:25:30,904 --> 00:25:33,321
Anything at all. Give me that.
I'll manage with that. Give it.

422
00:25:33,654 --> 00:25:37,154
See. When I asked for your
furniture you couldn't say a thing.

423
00:25:37,446 --> 00:25:40,738
Hey, should I come down?

424
00:25:41,238 --> 00:25:44,904
No. We don't call strangers
home at this hour. Go.

425
00:25:45,071 --> 00:25:46,279
I don't like this man.

426
00:25:46,321 --> 00:25:47,529
He can cause us trouble in the future.

427
00:25:47,571 --> 00:25:49,904
Should I teach him a lesson?
- Forget it.

428
00:25:50,571 --> 00:25:51,738
He's a frustrated man.

429
00:25:51,821 --> 00:25:53,279
He must have some problem as well.

430
00:25:55,320 --> 00:25:56,613
Tell me something.

431
00:25:57,654 --> 00:25:59,821
Is that girl really beautiful?

432
00:26:00,863 --> 00:26:02,196
She is.

433
00:26:05,279 --> 00:26:06,571
But I made a mistake.

434
00:26:06,738 --> 00:26:09,196
I didn't praise her.
- You did the right thing.

435
00:26:09,571 --> 00:26:10,779
The more negative you behave..

436
00:26:10,863 --> 00:26:11,946
..she'll be more impressed.

437
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:13,446
One more thing.

438
00:26:13,613 --> 00:26:15,321
She should think that..

439
00:26:15,404 --> 00:26:17,654
..that several girls
are crazy over you.

440
00:26:30,946 --> 00:26:33,238
I knew it.

441
00:26:33,363 --> 00:26:34,571
What is this?

442
00:26:34,821 --> 00:26:36,738
What is this? - My heart.

443
00:26:37,571 --> 00:26:38,946
Can't you girls think of anything..

444
00:26:39,029 --> 00:26:40,863
..other than love and heart?

445
00:26:40,946 --> 00:26:42,154
Explain to your friends.

446
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:45,779
What does he think of himself?

447
00:26:46,071 --> 00:26:47,363
There's something about him..

448
00:26:47,446 --> 00:26:50,154
..that's why 150 girls
are crazy about him.

449
00:26:50,738 --> 00:26:54,238
Excuse me. - Thank God.

450
00:26:54,529 --> 00:26:56,529
We won't have to give
this month's installment.

451
00:26:56,571 --> 00:26:59,529
Oh God, now you don't say
that you're in love with me.

452
00:26:59,571 --> 00:27:01,863
Please. - Me, with you?

453
00:27:02,238 --> 00:27:03,988
No way. - God is great.

454
00:27:04,071 --> 00:27:05,321
At least I found one girl..

455
00:27:05,404 --> 00:27:07,279
..who thinks about
other things than love.

456
00:27:07,529 --> 00:27:10,113
What's bad about her?
- What's good about her?

457
00:27:10,196 --> 00:27:11,529
She thinks she's beautiful.

458
00:27:12,738 --> 00:27:15,529
Beauty should be.. - Like me.

459
00:27:16,946 --> 00:27:20,279
No. You have shortcomings
as well. - Like?

460
00:27:20,446 --> 00:27:23,696
Look, your face is fine at the top..

461
00:27:23,779 --> 00:27:26,154
..but the problem starts
as we come down, isn't it?

462
00:27:26,363 --> 00:27:28,321
The nose could be sharper.

463
00:27:34,904 --> 00:27:38,321
Actually, you know beauty
isn't about the face alone.

464
00:27:38,404 --> 00:27:40,446
No, no, it's just about the face.

465
00:27:40,779 --> 00:27:43,988
Look at your face.
You look so handsome. - I know.

466
00:27:44,071 --> 00:27:47,613
I am very handsome. - Bye. - Bye.

467
00:27:57,446 --> 00:27:59,696
Hello. - Hello, hello, hello.

468
00:27:59,779 --> 00:28:04,904
Look.. I am not responsible
for whatever happened.

469
00:28:04,988 --> 00:28:06,320
You are responsible.

470
00:28:06,363 --> 00:28:08,320
Your entire face has been blackened.
- No, no, no.

471
00:28:08,363 --> 00:28:10,779
My friend did it. - Friend.

472
00:28:11,320 --> 00:28:13,613
Those two scoundrels
met me as friends as well..

473
00:28:13,654 --> 00:28:16,446
..and dishonored me in
front of the entire village.

474
00:28:16,821 --> 00:28:20,154
And that's why, whenever
I see someone with a black face..

475
00:28:20,238 --> 00:28:22,071
..I see myself.

476
00:28:22,238 --> 00:28:23,320
See. See.

477
00:28:23,363 --> 00:28:24,571
No, no, no.

478
00:28:24,654 --> 00:28:27,196
I will clean it, okay. - No.

479
00:28:27,446 --> 00:28:29,529
It's my face. I like it black.

480
00:28:29,613 --> 00:28:31,529
What's your problem?
- I do have a problem.

481
00:28:31,571 --> 00:28:35,320
Ever since I've been dishonored,
I hate black faces.

482
00:28:37,738 --> 00:28:40,529
You hate black. - I hate black.

483
00:28:42,446 --> 00:28:44,029
He hates black.

484
00:28:44,571 --> 00:28:47,238
What's wrong with you?
What the.. - He hates black.

485
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:49,738
No, no, no.. - You hate black.

486
00:28:49,988 --> 00:28:53,279
No, I.. - Obama is the president
of America and you still hate us?

487
00:28:53,321 --> 00:28:56,029
Look.. I said.. black face.

488
00:28:56,446 --> 00:28:57,779
Not the full body.

489
00:28:58,363 --> 00:29:00,446
He hates black. He hates black.

490
00:29:03,320 --> 00:29:04,529
So bad.

491
00:29:07,988 --> 00:29:10,196
Excuse me, why is there
a crowd gathered around here?

492
00:29:10,821 --> 00:29:12,904
Some Afro-American
people beat up an Indian.

493
00:29:13,404 --> 00:29:15,779
This used to happen in Australia.

494
00:29:16,071 --> 00:29:17,196
It has started here as well.

495
00:29:17,446 --> 00:29:18,529
Great.

496
00:29:20,613 --> 00:29:23,446
Seems like he's been badly beaten up.

497
00:29:23,654 --> 00:29:25,821
Get up, Brother. Get up.

498
00:29:30,154 --> 00:29:31,320
You recognized me?

499
00:29:33,821 --> 00:29:35,738
Who won't recognize an angel?

500
00:29:35,904 --> 00:29:38,696
You're the only one who
stepped forth to help me.

501
00:29:39,863 --> 00:29:41,238
Can't you see?

502
00:29:41,946 --> 00:29:43,529
My sight's distorted.

503
00:29:43,946 --> 00:29:45,571
Those scoundrels beat me up so badly.

504
00:29:47,113 --> 00:29:48,321
How many fingers?

505
00:29:50,196 --> 00:29:52,654
First take off your socks.

506
00:29:53,238 --> 00:29:55,613
Why are you joking with me?
- That's good.

507
00:29:55,779 --> 00:29:58,321
Come. Let's take you to the hospital,
Zandu Lal.

508
00:29:58,904 --> 00:30:00,113
Just a minute.

509
00:30:00,320 --> 00:30:01,988
How do you know my name?

510
00:30:02,779 --> 00:30:04,529
Your news was in the newspapers.

511
00:30:04,863 --> 00:30:07,363
You robbed a bank in the village,
isn't it? - No.

512
00:30:08,029 --> 00:30:09,738
- It's been published here as well.
- What's going on?

513
00:30:09,821 --> 00:30:11,571
Why is there a crowd?
What's happening?

514
00:30:12,154 --> 00:30:13,320
Clear! Clear!

515
00:30:14,154 --> 00:30:15,446
Come on, move.

516
00:30:16,113 --> 00:30:18,738
- Yash. You here? - Sir.

517
00:30:19,113 --> 00:30:21,154
How's your social work?
- Doing fine, sir.

518
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:22,863
And your friend.

519
00:30:23,113 --> 00:30:24,904
That cheater, thief, blackmailer.

520
00:30:25,279 --> 00:30:28,196
What is this, Yash?
You're such a decent man.

521
00:30:28,696 --> 00:30:30,529
Why do you keep the
company of that blackmailer?

522
00:30:30,738 --> 00:30:33,904
Leave him.
- Sir, can you leave your dog?

523
00:30:33,988 --> 00:30:35,571
No, no, no way.

524
00:30:35,904 --> 00:30:38,029
So. He's human after all.

525
00:30:38,613 --> 00:30:39,904
I've raised him.

526
00:30:39,988 --> 00:30:41,154
I'm trying to reform him,
sir, and I'll succeed.

527
00:30:41,238 --> 00:30:43,029
Hey, you can reform the world later..

528
00:30:43,113 --> 00:30:44,320
..first take care of my condition.

529
00:30:44,363 --> 00:30:45,946
Yes, come on. - Sir, I..

530
00:30:46,029 --> 00:30:47,446
No, I am going that way.
I'll drop him there.

531
00:30:47,779 --> 00:30:49,029
Okay, bye. - Okay, sir.

532
00:30:49,446 --> 00:30:50,613
Thank you.

533
00:30:51,696 --> 00:30:53,279
Yash, where were you?

534
00:30:53,321 --> 00:30:55,071
You know Zandu Lal is in the city.

535
00:30:55,279 --> 00:30:57,738
You met him as well.
- What do you mean? You too.

536
00:30:57,821 --> 00:31:00,154
This bank heist will ruin our lives.

537
00:31:01,196 --> 00:31:02,529
Damn this neighbor..

538
00:31:04,238 --> 00:31:06,779
Why are you disposing
your skirt in our house?

539
00:31:07,404 --> 00:31:11,029
Skirt? You're mistaking
my loincloth for a skirt.

540
00:31:11,279 --> 00:31:12,571
I was keeping it out to dry.
There was a gush of wind..

541
00:31:12,654 --> 00:31:14,363
..and it flew away. - Hey..

542
00:31:14,988 --> 00:31:17,029
Dry your clothes inside.

543
00:31:17,113 --> 00:31:20,154
If you have a problem
with my wet clothes..

544
00:31:20,238 --> 00:31:21,696
..then I'll send them to your home.

545
00:31:21,946 --> 00:31:24,279
Dry them, iron them and
send it back on a hangar.

546
00:31:24,321 --> 00:31:26,238
Do you think we're washer-men?

547
00:31:26,363 --> 00:31:27,613
What should we do with him?

548
00:31:27,779 --> 00:31:28,904
Tear it. - Tear it?

549
00:31:28,988 --> 00:31:30,071
Tear it.

550
00:31:30,279 --> 00:31:31,946
No, no.

551
00:31:34,238 --> 00:31:36,071
That was my honeymoon loincloth.

552
00:31:36,279 --> 00:31:37,363
Scoundrels.

553
00:31:37,446 --> 00:31:39,529
This city has troubled me a lot.

554
00:31:42,904 --> 00:31:44,654
Oh, God.
It hit him. - He's gone today.

555
00:31:45,196 --> 00:31:46,404
I won't spare him.

556
00:31:49,279 --> 00:31:51,029
Why are you hiding inside now?

557
00:31:51,196 --> 00:31:53,863
Come out. - I am not hiding.

558
00:31:54,404 --> 00:31:56,029
I am searching for my gun.

559
00:31:56,529 --> 00:31:58,696
I came here to murder two people.

560
00:31:58,946 --> 00:32:00,363
If I have to kill four,
there's no problem.

561
00:32:01,363 --> 00:32:03,029
Come back, Raj. He's hiding.

562
00:32:03,113 --> 00:32:05,113
I am sparing you for
the sake of my friend.

563
00:32:05,279 --> 00:32:07,863
Who are you trying to scare?

564
00:32:08,446 --> 00:32:10,446
Come on, I'll deal
with both of you. Come on.

565
00:32:14,904 --> 00:32:16,529
He's coming. He will do what he said.

566
00:32:19,071 --> 00:32:20,738
Come down, we're here.

567
00:32:20,821 --> 00:32:21,946
Deal with us.

568
00:32:22,654 --> 00:32:25,988
Can't you find the gun?
- I've found my gun but..

569
00:32:26,363 --> 00:32:27,988
Today is Tuesday.

570
00:32:28,571 --> 00:32:30,738
And I don't commit
murders on a Tuesday.

571
00:32:30,821 --> 00:32:32,404
You're fortunate.

572
00:32:32,613 --> 00:32:34,071
You survived.

573
00:32:34,946 --> 00:32:36,613
Let's go. Come on.

574
00:32:36,904 --> 00:32:38,779
Firstly,
Zandu is in the city and now him.

575
00:32:38,946 --> 00:32:40,363
Why are you worried?

576
00:32:40,446 --> 00:32:42,029
It's a big city. How can he find us?

577
00:32:42,238 --> 00:32:43,988
He'll wander around
for a few days and leave.

578
00:32:44,071 --> 00:32:45,613
He isn't hovering around us, come on.

579
00:33:09,988 --> 00:33:12,404
Why did you all come here?
- We had to.

580
00:33:13,113 --> 00:33:16,904
You don't come meet
us or attend our calls.

581
00:33:16,988 --> 00:33:18,196
I have so many things on my plate.

582
00:33:18,613 --> 00:33:19,779
I don't even get time to breathe.

583
00:33:19,863 --> 00:33:21,279
But you've got time to play.

584
00:33:21,904 --> 00:33:22,988
Who are you talking to?

585
00:33:23,071 --> 00:33:25,696
Mind your language.
- Don't shout at Marcos.

586
00:33:29,446 --> 00:33:32,529
Marcos, you've been
working with us for years.

587
00:33:32,863 --> 00:33:34,279
Why are you so impatient today?

588
00:33:34,321 --> 00:33:35,696
Those diamonds are worth millions.

589
00:33:36,279 --> 00:33:37,613
It can change anyone's intentions.

590
00:33:37,696 --> 00:33:39,654
And it's been so long
since I gave you the diamonds.

591
00:33:39,738 --> 00:33:41,529
Marcos, it's a big deal.

592
00:33:41,571 --> 00:33:43,154
It's bound to take time. - Two days.

593
00:33:43,529 --> 00:33:45,321
I give you only two days.

594
00:33:46,904 --> 00:33:50,529
The third day.. will be your last.

595
00:33:59,821 --> 00:34:01,779
This man can be a problem for you.

596
00:34:04,904 --> 00:34:08,779
And you know I don't like problems.

597
00:34:12,988 --> 00:34:15,779
Richard,
I need your casino at any cost.

598
00:34:19,113 --> 00:34:23,404
Marcos, the Riveir is the most
expensive casino in all of Vegas.

599
00:34:23,779 --> 00:34:25,446
You'll get your money in two days.

600
00:34:25,571 --> 00:34:26,738
Two days.

601
00:34:28,363 --> 00:34:32,238
Go, go. - Move, come on.

602
00:34:37,946 --> 00:34:40,196
Boss, they are minister's men. Run.

603
00:34:40,279 --> 00:34:43,154
Come on. Come on. Come on, fast.
- Come on. Come on, fast.

604
00:34:48,654 --> 00:34:49,988
Seems like the movie has started, sir.

605
00:34:50,071 --> 00:34:51,613
Listen to the sound quality, Naidu.

606
00:34:51,863 --> 00:34:53,779
It seems like someone's
shooting outside.

607
00:34:55,654 --> 00:34:58,320
Someone is really shooting.

608
00:34:58,779 --> 00:34:59,988
But we don't have backup again, sir.

609
00:35:00,071 --> 00:35:01,613
We don't need it.

610
00:35:03,571 --> 00:35:05,696
Come on. Move fast. Naidu.

611
00:35:10,863 --> 00:35:11,988
Sir, sir, sir, sir.

612
00:35:12,988 --> 00:35:15,696
Naidu. Naidu.

613
00:35:19,571 --> 00:35:21,071
Superman. Naidu.

614
00:35:24,738 --> 00:35:26,446
Sir, bullets are being
fired from both sides, sir.

615
00:35:26,654 --> 00:35:28,779
If I get hit I will die, sir.

616
00:35:29,154 --> 00:35:30,613
Please cover me, sir.

617
00:35:30,696 --> 00:35:33,154
If I cover you, who will cover me?

618
00:35:33,238 --> 00:35:35,446
Sir, you're used to taking bullets.

619
00:35:35,654 --> 00:35:36,946
There are already two bullets inside.

620
00:35:37,029 --> 00:35:38,904
It won't make a difference
if you're hit by a few more, sir.

621
00:35:41,320 --> 00:35:42,696
Come on, move. Move. Move. Move.

622
00:35:45,320 --> 00:35:48,029
Help! Help!

623
00:35:48,654 --> 00:35:51,738
Help!

624
00:36:04,613 --> 00:36:05,863
Marcos.

625
00:36:11,529 --> 00:36:13,196
Thank you. - Sir!

626
00:36:16,196 --> 00:36:17,279
Sir.

627
00:36:18,904 --> 00:36:20,071
Sir.

628
00:36:21,446 --> 00:36:24,696
Sir, any amount of
praise is less for you.

629
00:36:25,571 --> 00:36:29,654
It seems like a lion is
holding its prey in its claws.

630
00:36:30,571 --> 00:36:33,196
Yash, Arjun caught Marcos.

631
00:36:33,363 --> 00:36:36,154
Strange.
Even I couldn't understand that.

632
00:36:36,238 --> 00:36:37,613
Yes, sir. I am coming tomorrow.

633
00:36:37,863 --> 00:36:39,154
And I am completely assured..

634
00:36:39,238 --> 00:36:40,779
..that you'll take
care of me for good.

635
00:36:40,946 --> 00:36:42,071
Thank you. Thank you.

636
00:36:42,821 --> 00:36:45,529
"I won't leave you today.."

637
00:36:47,154 --> 00:36:49,738
Excuse me, there's a power failure..

638
00:36:49,904 --> 00:36:51,320
..and I can't see
anything in the dark.

639
00:36:51,446 --> 00:36:53,404
My house is closeby.
Will you take me there?

640
00:36:53,863 --> 00:36:55,654
I have an important work tomorrow.
I need to leave early.

641
00:36:55,738 --> 00:36:57,696
Come. - Thank you.

642
00:36:57,779 --> 00:37:00,363
By the way, what's the job..

643
00:37:00,446 --> 00:37:01,946
..that's making you jump
with joy even before it's finished?

644
00:37:03,904 --> 00:37:06,196
Two people are going to die tomorrow.

645
00:37:06,529 --> 00:37:07,988
Two people are going to die. - Yes.

646
00:37:08,071 --> 00:37:09,988
And you're celebrating.
- Why shouldn't I?

647
00:37:10,404 --> 00:37:12,196
They were both rascals.

648
00:37:12,363 --> 00:37:14,696
They came to my village
and robbed my bank.

649
00:37:17,196 --> 00:37:18,529
It's him. It's him. - What?

650
00:37:18,571 --> 00:37:20,946
I mean.. Uncle, how did you find out..

651
00:37:21,029 --> 00:37:22,446
..that those two rascals
live in this city?

652
00:37:22,571 --> 00:37:25,738
Those fools..
left their bag in my house.

653
00:37:25,821 --> 00:37:27,571
You left the bag there? - Yes.

654
00:37:28,279 --> 00:37:30,446
And tomorrow those
two will be in my clutches.

655
00:37:30,571 --> 00:37:32,446
How is that?
- Their photographs were in the bag.

656
00:37:32,654 --> 00:37:34,154
There were photographs
in the bag? - No

657
00:37:34,446 --> 00:37:36,321
No, he's right. There weren't
any photographs in the bag.

658
00:37:36,696 --> 00:37:38,404
I remember their faces clearly.

659
00:37:38,571 --> 00:37:40,904
I've captured it in my eyes,
like a wounded snake does.

660
00:37:41,738 --> 00:37:44,654
I thought of getting their
sketches made by an artist.

661
00:37:44,738 --> 00:37:47,738
But Mr. Arjun advised me that..
- Who Mr. Arjun?

662
00:37:47,946 --> 00:37:49,863
Police inspector Mr. Arjun.

663
00:37:50,154 --> 00:37:51,571
He's a famous inspector.

664
00:37:51,654 --> 00:37:54,154
He said, "Don't worry, don't worry."

665
00:37:54,696 --> 00:37:55,988
"The police records
have the photographs.."

666
00:37:56,071 --> 00:37:57,863
"..of all the criminals of the city."

667
00:37:57,946 --> 00:37:59,029
Come home and I'll show it to you.

668
00:37:59,113 --> 00:38:00,363
It must surely have my photograph.

669
00:38:01,029 --> 00:38:03,404
Feels like I've come to my home.

670
00:38:03,529 --> 00:38:04,779
That's the one.

671
00:38:04,988 --> 00:38:06,571
You live in that house?

672
00:38:07,071 --> 00:38:08,779
And that house which you see..

673
00:38:09,071 --> 00:38:10,654
That's where those
two scoundrels live.

674
00:38:10,738 --> 00:38:11,863
Come out!

675
00:38:12,529 --> 00:38:14,529
You dare call my loincloth a skirt!

676
00:38:15,320 --> 00:38:17,154
Tomorrow I am going
to see the inspector..

677
00:38:17,238 --> 00:38:20,071
..and turn your pants
into a skirt. Yes.

678
00:38:20,946 --> 00:38:23,071
Once I get hold of
those two scoundrels..

679
00:38:23,154 --> 00:38:25,529
..then I'll deal with these two.

680
00:38:26,029 --> 00:38:27,446
Thank you. Thank you.

681
00:38:27,529 --> 00:38:28,696
Good night.

682
00:38:29,446 --> 00:38:33,863
When he finds out we'll
have nowhere to run.

683
00:38:34,946 --> 00:38:37,404
Madam, where should I
throw this bouquet? - Throw it?

684
00:38:37,696 --> 00:38:38,946
Keep it here.

685
00:38:40,863 --> 00:38:43,654
What's wrong, Naidu?
- My photo wasn't published.

686
00:38:44,696 --> 00:38:45,821
Of course it will be published.

687
00:38:45,904 --> 00:38:47,696
You do something brave as well.

688
00:38:47,988 --> 00:38:49,613
What did sir do?

689
00:38:49,821 --> 00:38:51,613
We fell on Marcos together.

690
00:38:52,321 --> 00:38:53,404
Fell on him, what do you mean?

691
00:38:53,696 --> 00:38:55,571
Marcos was lying unconscious.

692
00:38:55,904 --> 00:38:59,238
Sir just kept his feet on
him and got his photos clicked.

693
00:38:59,404 --> 00:39:01,904
I was there as well.
But he pushed me away.

694
00:39:02,696 --> 00:39:03,821
Look.

695
00:39:04,238 --> 00:39:06,320
That half-a-head you see is mine.

696
00:39:07,113 --> 00:39:08,904
..did something brave..

697
00:39:18,613 --> 00:39:20,946
Mr. Zandu Lal, you came to the
right place. Your job will be done.

698
00:39:21,029 --> 00:39:22,279
Thank you.

699
00:39:22,321 --> 00:39:24,571
"No problem."

700
00:39:25,821 --> 00:39:27,238
Oh, God. - What happened?

701
00:39:28,029 --> 00:39:29,529
As soon as I thought
of those two scoundrels..

702
00:39:29,613 --> 00:39:31,613
..their images flashed before my eyes.

703
00:39:31,863 --> 00:39:33,488
It seemed as if they
just walked past this way.

704
00:39:35,404 --> 00:39:37,529
Which way? - This way. Behind you.

705
00:39:38,363 --> 00:39:40,529
What's the point of stealing here?

706
00:39:40,613 --> 00:39:43,946
That's how the inspector will
be degraded in front of Zandu Lal.

707
00:39:44,029 --> 00:39:46,529
He's been rewarded handsomely
for capturing Marcos. - Yes.

708
00:39:46,613 --> 00:39:47,863
The money is in this safe.

709
00:39:48,071 --> 00:39:51,404
I admit it wasn't just difficult,
but impossible to catch Marcos.

710
00:39:51,571 --> 00:39:54,529
The government has rewarded
me for my bravery..

711
00:39:54,613 --> 00:39:55,821
Hello, Sister-in-law. Hello.

712
00:39:55,904 --> 00:39:58,779
You're fortunate to have a husband
like him. - It was my duty, sir.

713
00:39:58,863 --> 00:40:00,863
He isn't just your
husband but God. Look.

714
00:40:01,154 --> 00:40:03,279
He's a brave man. A brave man. Look.

715
00:40:05,446 --> 00:40:07,529
Sister-in-law. - Why you..

716
00:40:07,988 --> 00:40:09,863
What's this?

717
00:40:09,946 --> 00:40:12,904
From which angle does he look brave?

718
00:40:13,571 --> 00:40:15,571
Brave. - No. No.

719
00:40:16,320 --> 00:40:18,154
Run. Run. Hide.

720
00:40:19,779 --> 00:40:20,946
We are done for.

721
00:40:23,196 --> 00:40:25,071
Hide quickly, hide.

722
00:40:25,363 --> 00:40:27,696
Not there. - Inside. Quickly.

723
00:40:27,779 --> 00:40:30,613
Help! Help!

724
00:40:30,988 --> 00:40:32,113
Open the door.

725
00:40:34,738 --> 00:40:36,779
There's place here.
- Only for one, come on. - Okay.

726
00:40:38,529 --> 00:40:40,863
"No problem."

727
00:40:42,113 --> 00:40:43,279
What's going on outside?

728
00:40:43,321 --> 00:40:44,613
Sister-in-law has been
graced by the 'Devi' (Goddess).

729
00:40:44,779 --> 00:40:46,571
Which one?
Sridevi. - The Goddess of death.

730
00:40:52,196 --> 00:40:53,363
Papa, quiet.

731
00:40:55,154 --> 00:40:56,529
Bullets are speaking.

732
00:41:02,320 --> 00:41:03,988
Seems like she's in this room.

733
00:41:05,320 --> 00:41:07,154
Throw him out. - Who? Who?

734
00:41:07,238 --> 00:41:08,321
You.

735
00:41:10,154 --> 00:41:13,988
Help! Help!

736
00:41:15,320 --> 00:41:17,696
"No problem."

737
00:41:27,821 --> 00:41:29,613
How much more will you deceive me?

738
00:41:29,779 --> 00:41:32,404
Kajal made sweet porridge and you..

739
00:41:34,363 --> 00:41:36,363
Eat the porridge.
- It's hot. It's hot.

740
00:41:36,446 --> 00:41:39,113
Eat it hot. - Eat it, Papa.

741
00:41:39,196 --> 00:41:40,279
Eat it, Papa.

742
00:41:40,613 --> 00:41:42,113
Otherwise we'll have to have it.

743
00:41:45,113 --> 00:41:46,238
Eat it.

744
00:41:46,320 --> 00:41:47,988
Eat some more.

745
00:41:54,529 --> 00:41:56,946
Why are you eating like this?

746
00:41:57,238 --> 00:41:59,320
And so hot. - She's fine now.

747
00:41:59,363 --> 00:42:00,654
I'll feed you properly.

748
00:42:01,113 --> 00:42:02,654
Ma'am.

749
00:42:02,904 --> 00:42:06,071
There's been a robbery.
- What? Robbery?

750
00:42:06,696 --> 00:42:10,363
Papa, there's been a robbery.

751
00:42:11,279 --> 00:42:13,029
The reward for catching
Marcos is gone.

752
00:42:13,446 --> 00:42:15,988
Inform the police.
- Police? - Yes, police.

753
00:42:16,238 --> 00:42:18,779
You're a police inspector
and I am the commissioner.

754
00:42:18,988 --> 00:42:20,696
We'll be defamed.

755
00:42:21,113 --> 00:42:24,904
Brother, you need more help.

756
00:42:25,321 --> 00:42:28,321
At least keep a dog that
barks on seeing the thieves..

757
00:42:28,404 --> 00:42:29,613
..and not when they leave.

758
00:42:29,821 --> 00:42:31,404
And keep some bodyguards too..

759
00:42:31,529 --> 00:42:33,529
..who can protect you from your wife.

760
00:42:33,904 --> 00:42:37,446
And stop publishing fake
photographs in the newspapers.

761
00:42:37,738 --> 00:42:41,363
People get happy pointlessly.
Brave man.

762
00:42:41,613 --> 00:42:43,779
You're not even half the man.

763
00:42:44,113 --> 00:42:46,738
You aren't worthy of
being in the post office.

764
00:42:47,529 --> 00:42:52,071
Whenever Kajal turns into
Kamini I have to face slander.

765
00:42:52,654 --> 00:42:54,571
If I didn't love Kajal..

766
00:42:54,654 --> 00:42:56,988
..I would've strangled her to death.

767
00:43:00,321 --> 00:43:02,654
What's wrong? Why are you laughing?

768
00:43:02,821 --> 00:43:04,363
Ms. Universe's photo
has been published.

769
00:43:05,404 --> 00:43:07,029
Look.

770
00:43:07,320 --> 00:43:10,029
They make just anyone.. Ms. Universe.

771
00:43:10,113 --> 00:43:13,029
Somebody help!
These girls are committing suicide.

772
00:43:13,321 --> 00:43:16,071
Come on, hurry up!

773
00:43:16,738 --> 00:43:21,113
Oh, my God.
O God! Stop! Somebody stop them.

774
00:43:21,446 --> 00:43:23,238
Somebody help!

775
00:43:26,196 --> 00:43:29,029
I want to die.
Leave me. - Come out, come out.

776
00:43:29,529 --> 00:43:31,529
No, I don't want to live.
- Why do you want to die?

777
00:43:31,613 --> 00:43:33,696
Leave me. - Come out.

778
00:43:34,363 --> 00:43:35,613
Shut up!

779
00:43:35,904 --> 00:43:37,988
Why are all you girls
committing mass suicide?

780
00:43:39,738 --> 00:43:40,988
Because of him.

781
00:43:42,321 --> 00:43:45,196
All of us love him so much.

782
00:43:45,279 --> 00:43:48,529
And today we found out
that he loves some Sanjana.

783
00:43:48,946 --> 00:43:50,363
Sanjana? - Yes.

784
00:43:50,571 --> 00:43:52,446
He says she's the most
beautiful girl in the world.

785
00:43:52,571 --> 00:43:54,696
Look at me. What's missing in me?

786
00:43:54,779 --> 00:43:56,238
I am Ms. Durban.

787
00:43:57,113 --> 00:43:58,238
How did you become?

788
00:43:58,821 --> 00:43:59,904
What?

789
00:44:00,404 --> 00:44:02,279
I mean how did you get fooled?

790
00:44:02,779 --> 00:44:05,279
What's so special about him?
- Take a closer look.

791
00:44:05,321 --> 00:44:06,613
He's got everything.

792
00:44:06,946 --> 00:44:09,696
My heart starts pounding
in his presence.

793
00:44:09,863 --> 00:44:12,404
But if he loves Sanjana
then why hasn't he told her yet?

794
00:44:12,529 --> 00:44:15,363
He will tell her. Do you
know about his ego, his arrogance?

795
00:44:16,279 --> 00:44:18,529
He'd rather die than say 'I love you'.

796
00:44:18,571 --> 00:44:20,321
Sanjana will have to say it.

797
00:44:25,529 --> 00:44:27,738
Come on, round them up. - Come on.

798
00:44:27,821 --> 00:44:30,446
Break it up, come on break it up.

799
00:44:30,821 --> 00:44:33,821
Come on, take them inside.

800
00:44:36,988 --> 00:44:40,404
Sir, I am not one of them.

801
00:44:40,988 --> 00:44:43,238
I come from a decent home. - I see.

802
00:44:43,529 --> 00:44:44,571
Where is your home?

803
00:44:44,654 --> 00:44:46,904
'If this scoundrel
finds out the truth..'

804
00:44:46,988 --> 00:44:48,904
'..then I'll have to spend
the entire night in prison.'

805
00:44:49,446 --> 00:44:51,071
You're from a decent
family and you don't go home.

806
00:44:51,404 --> 00:44:54,738
Tell me, would you prefer
the lock-up or my home?

807
00:44:56,154 --> 00:44:59,196
Sir? - Don't worry,
my wife's visiting her parents.

808
00:45:01,071 --> 00:45:03,571
Don't stare,
Naidu, you know I am a decent man.

809
00:45:04,238 --> 00:45:06,571
But.. my girlfriend before Kajal..

810
00:45:07,404 --> 00:45:10,821
..looked.. just like her.

811
00:45:12,238 --> 00:45:13,404
Come, baby. Come.

812
00:45:13,571 --> 00:45:15,529
Your girlfriend was manly.

813
00:45:23,529 --> 00:45:26,113
Careful,
the wig might come off. - What?

814
00:45:26,779 --> 00:45:31,029
I mean.. I might go out of breath.

815
00:45:31,613 --> 00:45:37,988
Oh my.. that's the grace which..
wives lack.

816
00:45:39,988 --> 00:45:41,154
Come.

817
00:45:42,571 --> 00:45:43,946
My dear..

818
00:45:44,238 --> 00:45:47,904
You have a beautiful
wife and a cute child.

819
00:45:48,154 --> 00:45:50,654
Why do you men always do this?

820
00:45:51,571 --> 00:45:54,863
Men are dogs. - Yes.

821
00:45:55,320 --> 00:45:56,946
But I am helpless.

822
00:45:57,613 --> 00:46:01,571
I haven't received my
wife's love for years. - What?

823
00:46:01,946 --> 00:46:04,529
One day we were making love..

824
00:46:04,863 --> 00:46:06,529
..and she had a fit.

825
00:46:06,613 --> 00:46:08,321
Split personality.

826
00:46:10,529 --> 00:46:13,113
I didn't realize
when she broke my head..

827
00:46:13,196 --> 00:46:14,571
..when blood starting oozing out.

828
00:46:14,696 --> 00:46:17,113
After that day, I couldn't muster
up the courage to go up to my wife.

829
00:46:18,904 --> 00:46:20,738
Oh my.

830
00:46:21,363 --> 00:46:23,613
You're really very sad.

831
00:46:24,279 --> 00:46:27,779
Come on, come on. Come.

832
00:46:29,029 --> 00:46:30,613
We'll see what happens.

833
00:46:30,946 --> 00:46:32,654
What do you mean by
'we'll see what happens'?

834
00:46:33,320 --> 00:46:34,529
I have AIDS.

835
00:46:36,196 --> 00:46:37,529
AIDS.

836
00:46:40,779 --> 00:46:41,863
Where are you going?

837
00:46:41,946 --> 00:46:43,696
To switch off the lights?
- No, Sister.

838
00:46:43,904 --> 00:46:45,446
To get a taxi for you?

839
00:46:47,446 --> 00:46:49,113
Yes, yes, yes.

840
00:46:51,446 --> 00:46:52,529
Surprise.

841
00:46:52,613 --> 00:46:55,113
How did you come back home?

842
00:46:55,196 --> 00:46:56,738
And Tuktuk? - What could I do?

843
00:46:56,821 --> 00:46:58,154
I was getting bored without you.

844
00:46:58,320 --> 00:46:59,404
But that Tuktuk..

845
00:46:59,571 --> 00:47:01,529
She insisted on staying
with her grandpa.

846
00:47:01,613 --> 00:47:03,904
So I left her there.
Anyway, I'll freshen up.

847
00:47:04,071 --> 00:47:06,529
Don't go inside. - Why?

848
00:47:06,613 --> 00:47:08,404
There's someone inside. - Who?

849
00:47:08,529 --> 00:47:10,238
Sister. I mean she's my sister.

850
00:47:11,363 --> 00:47:12,696
Sister? What do you mean?

851
00:47:12,779 --> 00:47:13,863
Hey!

852
00:47:16,946 --> 00:47:18,446
He's your sister?

853
00:47:18,821 --> 00:47:20,363
I am his friend, Sister-in-law.

854
00:47:20,654 --> 00:47:22,029
Actually he doesn't have a sister.

855
00:47:22,113 --> 00:47:23,946
Once I tied him the
sacred thread of 'Rakhi'.

856
00:47:24,029 --> 00:47:26,196
Since then he's been
calling me his sister.

857
00:47:26,696 --> 00:47:28,904
Thanks for the clothes, Arjun.
Mine got slightly spoiled.

858
00:47:29,279 --> 00:47:31,779
So nice to meet you.
I am leaving. - Nice meeting you.

859
00:47:32,863 --> 00:47:35,613
I am your father, get that.

860
00:47:36,779 --> 00:47:38,029
Okay. - Okay.

861
00:47:38,446 --> 00:47:39,904
Bye. - Bye.

862
00:47:45,988 --> 00:47:47,863
Hi, Raj. - Hi... - Hi.

863
00:47:48,071 --> 00:47:50,154
Aren't you attending the wedding?
- Whose wedding?

864
00:47:50,320 --> 00:47:51,571
Sanjana's.

865
00:47:51,904 --> 00:47:54,571
Come on, we're getting late.
- Let's go, let's go.

866
00:48:04,029 --> 00:48:07,738
Congrats, Sanjana. - Thank you.

867
00:48:18,279 --> 00:48:22,363
Hi. - Hi.
- Sorry, for this. - It's okay.

868
00:48:22,571 --> 00:48:24,863
You didn't invite me to your wedding.

869
00:48:25,071 --> 00:48:26,529
It all happened so suddenly.

870
00:48:26,571 --> 00:48:28,238
I forgot to invite so many friends.

871
00:48:28,738 --> 00:48:29,863
Who is the lucky one?

872
00:48:30,196 --> 00:48:31,904
He's your choice. Must be handsome.

873
00:48:32,238 --> 00:48:33,904
No, he's okay.

874
00:48:34,821 --> 00:48:36,113
You can consider it as a compromise.

875
00:48:36,279 --> 00:48:38,321
Compromise? - Of course.

876
00:48:39,321 --> 00:48:40,863
There's no one made for me.

877
00:48:41,113 --> 00:48:42,571
But he has one quality.

878
00:48:42,863 --> 00:48:44,613
He doesn't have an ego or arrogance.

879
00:48:44,696 --> 00:48:49,696
All the time he just keeps saying,
"I love you, Sanjana."

880
00:48:50,446 --> 00:48:52,238
Just because he says 'I
love you' you agreed to marry him?

881
00:48:52,363 --> 00:48:54,821
No, he does. - Even I..

882
00:48:55,238 --> 00:48:57,071
Yes, you were saying something.

883
00:48:58,029 --> 00:48:59,196
It's too late.

884
00:48:59,279 --> 00:49:00,696
We aren't married yet.

885
00:49:01,363 --> 00:49:02,654
It can be cancelled as well.

886
00:49:03,404 --> 00:49:05,321
What? - You don't know me.

887
00:49:05,404 --> 00:49:06,821
I am very crazy.

888
00:49:07,029 --> 00:49:11,363
And if I find someone better,
who loves me more then why not.

889
00:49:11,446 --> 00:49:13,654
Sanjana, I..I also really love you.

890
00:49:14,238 --> 00:49:16,571
Really. - Yes, I love you very much.

891
00:49:17,196 --> 00:49:20,321
But how did you suddenly..
- Not suddenly.

892
00:49:20,904 --> 00:49:22,529
Remember when we met the first time.

893
00:49:22,613 --> 00:49:25,863
"Television, plasma. Indica, Ferrari."

894
00:49:26,196 --> 00:49:27,279
That's when it happened.

895
00:49:27,779 --> 00:49:29,654
I swear that I love you.

896
00:49:30,529 --> 00:49:32,029
He said, "I love you."

897
00:49:32,238 --> 00:49:34,113
Let me get married now.

898
00:49:35,071 --> 00:49:37,446
She's getting married.
I asked her to get two gowns stitched.

899
00:49:37,696 --> 00:49:39,196
I have to make someone say I love you.

900
00:49:39,321 --> 00:49:40,404
Come on.

901
00:49:43,946 --> 00:49:45,904
She really is crazy.

902
00:49:46,988 --> 00:49:48,654
Papa, Raj is here.

903
00:49:48,988 --> 00:49:52,196
Welcome, welcome, welcome. Come in.

904
00:49:53,320 --> 00:49:57,154
Did you have to fall for the
commissioner's daughter? - Commissioner?

905
00:49:57,321 --> 00:49:58,779
You petty thief, have you ever..

906
00:49:58,863 --> 00:50:00,904
..seen anyone other than
the constable or inspector?

907
00:50:01,279 --> 00:50:04,863
I am Yash. Raj's elder brother.

908
00:50:05,320 --> 00:50:06,696
Yash Raj. - No, no, no.

909
00:50:06,779 --> 00:50:08,071
We don't have any
connection with them.

910
00:50:08,320 --> 00:50:10,529
We're Ambani's. - Ambani's.

911
00:50:10,613 --> 00:50:13,363
No, no, we don't have any
connection with them either.

912
00:50:13,821 --> 00:50:15,321
They're Indians and we're foreigners.

913
00:50:15,404 --> 00:50:18,113
NRI's. - Oh, I see.
Sit down, sit down.

914
00:50:18,196 --> 00:50:19,279
Papa, Raj was saying..

915
00:50:19,321 --> 00:50:20,946
..that he'll buy Reliance
as soon as we get married.

916
00:50:24,363 --> 00:50:25,571
Sit down, sir.

917
00:50:27,613 --> 00:50:29,238
Hello, sir. - Hello!

918
00:50:29,904 --> 00:50:31,071
"No problem."

919
00:50:32,321 --> 00:50:33,404
You?

920
00:50:33,654 --> 00:50:35,529
Ram Lal, you didn't
come see me this month.

921
00:50:35,779 --> 00:50:37,571
I haven't received my salary yet.

922
00:50:38,238 --> 00:50:39,363
You know my servant.

923
00:50:39,446 --> 00:50:42,529
Actually my younger
brother does social work.

924
00:50:43,154 --> 00:50:45,529
He has sympathy for poor people.

925
00:50:45,821 --> 00:50:47,946
Like servants, maids, cooks, driver.

926
00:50:48,571 --> 00:50:50,029
He's the support system of the poor.

927
00:50:50,238 --> 00:50:51,571
He takes away their money.

928
00:50:51,779 --> 00:50:53,071
To make a fixed deposit.

929
00:50:53,363 --> 00:50:55,154
I can't believe it.

930
00:50:55,738 --> 00:50:57,154
Do you have poison?

931
00:50:57,320 --> 00:50:59,321
Will cyanide do? - It will do fine.

932
00:50:59,696 --> 00:51:02,154
Let's mix it in Raj's
milkshake and give it to him.

933
00:51:02,904 --> 00:51:04,154
Grandpa.

934
00:51:04,238 --> 00:51:06,279
Sister and brother-in-law
are here as well.

935
00:51:06,529 --> 00:51:09,988
"No Problem. No Problem."

936
00:51:10,863 --> 00:51:12,071
Yash. Arjun.

937
00:51:12,154 --> 00:51:14,154
Only God can save you now.

938
00:51:16,238 --> 00:51:17,363
Where did he go?

939
00:51:17,571 --> 00:51:18,946
My brother is very religious.

940
00:51:19,154 --> 00:51:20,738
When he sees a temple..

941
00:51:20,821 --> 00:51:22,904
Yash, you? - Sir.

942
00:51:23,571 --> 00:51:24,779
You know him.

943
00:51:24,863 --> 00:51:27,404
Kajal, he's a big social
worker of the city.

944
00:51:27,529 --> 00:51:30,613
Greetings. - You were saying
that your brother is a social worker.

945
00:51:30,696 --> 00:51:31,821
He too, sir.

946
00:51:31,988 --> 00:51:33,654
He's a smaller one,
and I am slightly bigger.

947
00:51:33,738 --> 00:51:35,779
Save me from this rascal today, God.

948
00:51:35,863 --> 00:51:37,738
Yash, you never told me
that you have a younger brother.

949
00:51:37,946 --> 00:51:39,279
You never asked me, sir.

950
00:51:40,571 --> 00:51:43,571
Sir. - I swear on Sanjana,
I will stop everything from today.

951
00:51:43,738 --> 00:51:44,863
Stealing, blackmailing..

952
00:51:44,946 --> 00:51:46,904
You're getting the most
beautiful girl in the world..

953
00:51:46,988 --> 00:51:49,363
..what else are you asking God for?

954
00:51:52,404 --> 00:51:56,071
You! Scoundrel, rascal, how dare you!

955
00:51:56,154 --> 00:51:59,154
'Oh my.. that's the grace which..
wives lack.'

956
00:52:01,279 --> 00:52:03,363
I have the entire clip.

957
00:52:03,529 --> 00:52:05,863
You carry out raids
and take cheap woman home.

958
00:52:06,029 --> 00:52:07,946
Sanjana! - Quiet!

959
00:52:08,154 --> 00:52:09,613
If you say anything
else I will beat you.

960
00:52:09,696 --> 00:52:11,529
You never come to see your friend.

961
00:52:13,779 --> 00:52:16,071
And he's here to ask for
my sister-in-law's hand in marriage.

962
00:52:16,154 --> 00:52:17,404
And without telling me.

963
00:52:17,529 --> 00:52:19,529
Kajal, did you recognize him?
- I know.

964
00:52:19,613 --> 00:52:21,946
Of course she'll recognize me.
- How are you, Sister-in-law?

965
00:52:22,029 --> 00:52:23,363
Hi. My God.

966
00:52:23,488 --> 00:52:25,904
That's surprising.
Everyone knows each other.

967
00:52:25,988 --> 00:52:28,196
I know him too.
There's another one coming for you.

968
00:52:28,279 --> 00:52:30,196
This is special for Raj.

969
00:52:30,571 --> 00:52:32,404
Raj, this is for you especially.

970
00:52:32,529 --> 00:52:33,571
You forgot, didn't you, Ram Lal?

971
00:52:33,654 --> 00:52:37,238
It's Sunday today.
It's my day of fasting.

972
00:52:37,488 --> 00:52:39,904
'Scoundrel, curse you.'

973
00:52:40,029 --> 00:52:41,321
Sit down, sit down. Please sit down.

974
00:52:41,404 --> 00:52:42,946
'If this scoundrel becomes
a part of this family..'

975
00:52:43,029 --> 00:52:44,738
'..he'll ruin everyone.'

976
00:52:45,738 --> 00:52:47,779
The commissioner doesn't
see anyone without an appointment.

977
00:52:48,196 --> 00:52:49,363
Okay, will you do me a favor?

978
00:52:49,488 --> 00:52:52,238
Will you deliver these
two photographs to him?

979
00:52:52,320 --> 00:52:54,321
These two are inside. - Yes.

980
00:52:55,154 --> 00:52:57,821
And sir's younger daughter
is getting married to him.

981
00:53:01,321 --> 00:53:04,613
So, is this final?
- No problem from my side.

982
00:53:04,863 --> 00:53:06,320
Just Kajal and Arjun..

983
00:53:06,488 --> 00:53:07,571
What do you say, Arjun?

984
00:53:07,654 --> 00:53:09,863
I..I was thinking, Father..

985
00:53:11,029 --> 00:53:12,488
Thank God, it didn't break.

986
00:53:12,863 --> 00:53:14,321
Whatever is inside is safe. Safe.

987
00:53:14,404 --> 00:53:16,654
You were thinking about something.
- What's there to think?

988
00:53:16,904 --> 00:53:20,363
We often lose good boys if we think.
Like you.

989
00:53:20,488 --> 00:53:21,821
That's means this alliance
has been finalized.

990
00:53:21,904 --> 00:53:23,529
Let's have sweets.

991
00:53:23,613 --> 00:53:25,529
Have sweets. - These are fritters.

992
00:53:25,613 --> 00:53:26,863
Oh, sorry, sorry.

993
00:53:27,654 --> 00:53:30,238
Have sweets. Have sweets.

994
00:53:31,863 --> 00:53:34,779
No Problem, No Problem,

995
00:53:36,404 --> 00:53:37,172
What?

996
00:53:37,654 --> 00:53:40,213
What are you staring at?

997
00:53:40,904 --> 00:53:42,154
What did you think?

998
00:53:42,613 --> 00:53:44,321
You will run away from the
village and come to the city..

999
00:53:44,404 --> 00:53:45,779
..and I won't find you two.

1000
00:53:45,863 --> 00:53:48,529
You.. - Me. I am..

1001
00:53:48,613 --> 00:53:50,946
Uncle. Uncle. - Uncle.

1002
00:53:51,029 --> 00:53:53,863
Uncle, we love you. - Nephew. Nephew.

1003
00:53:54,488 --> 00:53:56,863
What did you think?
Uncle must be dead.

1004
00:53:57,113 --> 00:53:58,863
You two came here to
talk about your alliance.

1005
00:53:58,946 --> 00:54:00,613
You didn't even tell me.
- We made a mistake, uncle

1006
00:54:00,696 --> 00:54:03,071
Mistake, mistake. - It hurts.

1007
00:54:03,154 --> 00:54:04,613
Uncle, aren't you the one..

1008
00:54:05,029 --> 00:54:08,654
..whose bank was robbed
by two scoundrels? - Yes, yes.

1009
00:54:08,904 --> 00:54:10,696
Did you find them? - I found them.

1010
00:54:11,196 --> 00:54:12,946
The money? - I'll get that as well.

1011
00:54:13,321 --> 00:54:15,071
It's fine if they give it peacefully.

1012
00:54:15,404 --> 00:54:17,738
Otherwise, I've got the
police department with me.

1013
00:54:17,821 --> 00:54:19,988
We'll hang them upside
down and beat them.

1014
00:54:20,071 --> 00:54:21,320
Heard that. Heard that.

1015
00:54:21,363 --> 00:54:23,488
Uncle, let's not talk about this.

1016
00:54:23,571 --> 00:54:24,696
Meet your daughter-in-law.

1017
00:54:25,779 --> 00:54:28,196
Hello, Uncle. - Bless you, dear.

1018
00:54:28,363 --> 00:54:30,529
When have you scheduled
the engagement for?

1019
00:54:30,613 --> 00:54:32,196
Tomorrow is Sanjana's birthday.

1020
00:54:32,279 --> 00:54:33,529
With your permission tomorrow..

1021
00:54:33,613 --> 00:54:35,488
Fine, fine, fine. I accept.

1022
00:54:40,863 --> 00:54:44,196
You exist. You exist.

1023
00:54:44,821 --> 00:54:46,488
I had lost faith in You.

1024
00:54:48,029 --> 00:54:49,488
But He's there. - Yes, He's there..

1025
00:54:54,320 --> 00:54:57,029
Sometimes human beings
go crazy with happiness.

1026
00:54:57,113 --> 00:54:58,529
Also with sorrow.

1027
00:54:58,988 --> 00:55:00,321
Even I did.

1028
00:55:04,946 --> 00:55:07,904
First tell me.. where is my money?

1029
00:55:08,154 --> 00:55:09,320
We spent it.

1030
00:55:11,238 --> 00:55:12,263
You spent it.

1031
00:55:13,946 --> 00:55:15,096
All of it?

1032
00:55:15,738 --> 00:55:18,196
Actually,
Uncle, we robbed only one bank.

1033
00:55:18,529 --> 00:55:20,071
If we had robbed two or four banks..

1034
00:55:20,154 --> 00:55:21,463
..we would've spent that as well.

1035
00:55:21,488 --> 00:55:22,904
We're big spenders .

1036
00:55:25,696 --> 00:55:28,529
How will he get engaged?

1037
