1210
01:07:09,613 --> 01:07:10,738
What have we done?

1211
01:07:11,613 --> 01:07:13,238
Minister Sanyal's murder.

1212
01:07:13,320 --> 01:07:15,904
Murder? - What? - Murder?

1213
01:07:16,154 --> 01:07:17,738
Mr. Arjun,
we didn't commit any murder.

1214
01:07:17,821 --> 01:07:19,196
We only went there to steal.

1215
01:07:19,279 --> 01:07:20,488
What nonsense are you speaking?

1216
01:07:20,571 --> 01:07:21,946
They're accusing us of murder..

1217
01:07:22,029 --> 01:07:23,113
..that's why I am
telling them the truth.

1218
01:07:23,196 --> 01:07:24,488
Shut up. Shut up, please.

1219
01:07:25,738 --> 01:07:27,988
He's gone crazy with happiness. - Yes.

1220
01:07:28,154 --> 01:07:31,629
Mr. Arjun,
you know what a decent man I am.

1221
01:07:31,738 --> 01:07:34,113
Decent? This is your decency.

1222
01:07:36,779 --> 01:07:38,529
Take these glasses off.

1223
01:07:39,404 --> 01:07:41,571
Let me see your real face.

1224
01:07:42,925 --> 01:07:43,891
Boss.

1225
01:07:44,946 --> 01:07:48,320
Uncle? So you're their boss.

1226
01:07:48,363 --> 01:07:51,488
No, I am neither their
uncle nor their boss.

1227
01:07:51,654 --> 01:07:53,071
I am total loss, sir.

1228
01:07:53,154 --> 01:07:56,113
My wife, children, and the
entire village is waiting for me.

1229
01:07:56,380 --> 01:07:57,963
And it's time for my flight as well.

1230
01:07:57,988 --> 01:07:59,320
Sir, please let me go.

1231
01:07:59,363 --> 01:08:00,738
I haven't done anything.

1232
01:08:05,029 --> 01:08:06,488
Look, sir. Take a look yourself.

1233
01:08:06,529 --> 01:08:08,071
We only committed
a robbery and not murder.

1234
01:08:08,363 --> 01:08:10,029
Mr. Arjun, you've known me for years.

1235
01:08:10,238 --> 01:08:13,029
I am a petty thief,
I blackmail people. Remember.

1236
01:08:13,113 --> 01:08:14,238
Remember, sir.

1237
01:08:15,821 --> 01:08:18,654
Tell that to the court and not here.

1238
01:08:18,779 --> 01:08:20,029
Take them away. - Yes, sir.

1239
01:08:20,113 --> 01:08:22,321
Sister, look what
brother-in-law has done.

1240
01:08:24,988 --> 01:08:27,821
You knew that..
he was a thief, a blackmailer..

1241
01:08:27,904 --> 01:08:31,529
..but still you..
- Papa, I say let's forget the past.

1242
01:08:31,696 --> 01:08:34,446
And think that I took the
right action at the right time..

1243
01:08:34,488 --> 01:08:35,863
..and saved Sanjana's life.

1244
01:08:35,904 --> 01:08:38,821
You ruined it as well, rascal.

1245
01:08:39,821 --> 01:08:42,363
Wait! Take me along.

1246
01:08:42,738 --> 01:08:44,238
Take me along.

1247
01:08:55,760 --> 01:08:58,178
Until yesterday I
had only robbed a bank.

1248
01:08:58,678 --> 01:09:01,094
And today I've also
committed a murder.

1249
01:09:01,969 --> 01:09:03,344
A minister's murder.

1250
01:09:05,178 --> 01:09:08,069
Boss, you're confessing
in front of the police.

1251
01:09:08,094 --> 01:09:10,886
Did you commit the murder?
- I didn't rob the bank either.

1252
01:09:11,636 --> 01:09:13,219
But I've been accused of it.

1253
01:09:13,386 --> 01:09:16,136
Scoundrels.
I'm stuck in this because of you.

1254
01:09:16,219 --> 01:09:18,303
You two got me stuck in this.

1255
01:09:18,766 --> 01:09:20,683
It's your bank which he
robbed and I got stuck in it.

1256
01:09:20,719 --> 01:09:24,303
I was getting engaged,
but instead I got arrested.

1257
01:09:24,719 --> 01:09:28,719
You're putting the entire blame on me.

1258
01:09:29,386 --> 01:09:32,136
You wanted that crazy girl.
You wanted the money.

1259
01:09:32,219 --> 01:09:34,761
And I am stuck in all this,
trying to save you two.

1260
01:09:35,719 --> 01:09:38,053
I know that we three are stuck.

1261
01:09:38,469 --> 01:09:39,719
But I don't understand..

1262
01:09:39,760 --> 01:09:41,511
..who's responsible for it after all?

1263
01:09:42,428 --> 01:09:43,511
Why did it stop?

1264
01:09:45,011 --> 01:09:48,094
There's a shooting going on.
- Here, have sweets. Here.

1265
01:09:48,178 --> 01:09:50,803
That rascal blackmailer
has been arrested.

1266
01:09:50,886 --> 01:09:53,528
And his friend.
The decent one who wore spectacles.

1267
01:09:53,594 --> 01:09:54,886
He turned out to be a bigger conman.

1268
01:09:54,928 --> 01:09:57,886
Murderer. They'll be hanged. Hanged.

1269
01:09:58,718 --> 01:10:00,218
Brother, have sweets.

1270
01:10:00,301 --> 01:10:02,634
Here. Don't be shy. Have it.

1271
01:10:03,843 --> 01:10:05,843
You're distributing sweets.

1272
01:10:06,301 --> 01:10:09,218
He'll ruin your life
before getting hanged.

1273
01:10:09,551 --> 01:10:10,718
No, no, please.

1274
01:10:10,800 --> 01:10:13,134
I've thought of a scene for your film.

1275
01:10:13,718 --> 01:10:15,134
Come and meet us
at the police station.

1276
01:10:22,551 --> 01:10:24,718
What's wrong, sir?
Why are you so angry?

1277
01:10:24,968 --> 01:10:26,926
Those three ruined me.

1278
01:10:27,718 --> 01:10:29,718
The entire family is
asking me weird questions.

1279
01:10:29,743 --> 01:10:30,786
What answers should I give them?

1280
01:10:31,301 --> 01:10:32,926
Bring them to the torture room.
- Yes, sir.

1281
01:10:38,468 --> 01:10:40,384
Is there a shooting. - Yes, sir.

1282
01:10:46,051 --> 01:10:48,026
Actually,
sir, the director of this film..

1283
01:10:48,051 --> 01:10:49,634
..was looking for
an honest police officer.

1284
01:10:49,843 --> 01:10:52,926
And I said our sir would
be absolutely perfect for this role.

1285
01:10:53,718 --> 01:10:54,926
Would you like to work in films?

1286
01:10:55,843 --> 01:10:57,843
Of course I would.
- Do you have the passion?

1287
01:10:58,926 --> 01:11:00,926
Who doesn't? - Can you act?

1288
01:11:02,134 --> 01:11:03,468
It's the hero's role, sir.

1289
01:11:03,551 --> 01:11:04,618
What does he have to do after all?

1290
01:11:05,218 --> 01:11:07,218
Explain to him the
scene that I told you.

1291
01:11:07,301 --> 01:11:08,843
Is the lighting ready, Bhaskar?

1292
01:11:08,926 --> 01:11:10,843
Sir, there are three
inmates locked up here..

1293
01:11:10,926 --> 01:11:12,551
..and they've been
charged with murder.

1294
01:11:12,800 --> 01:11:14,551
But you know they're innocent.

1295
01:11:14,718 --> 01:11:16,301
You let those three flee from here.

1296
01:11:21,384 --> 01:11:23,384
It's a nice scene. - Nice, isn't it?

1297
01:11:23,800 --> 01:11:25,551
But who are these
three innocent inmates?

1298
01:11:25,718 --> 01:11:26,643
It's them, sir.

1299
01:11:31,999 --> 01:11:35,831
Them. Thief, blackmailer, murderer.
They're innocent.

1300
01:11:35,968 --> 01:11:38,718
They.. they wouldn't be
innocent even in their childhood.

1301
01:11:38,800 --> 01:11:40,134
But they are in the film.

1302
01:11:40,218 --> 01:11:41,718
In films what happens
doesn't happen actually..

1303
01:11:41,800 --> 01:11:43,551
..and what doesn't
happen is what happens.

1304
01:11:43,634 --> 01:11:46,551
They're culprits,
but in your view they're innocent.

1305
01:11:46,634 --> 01:11:48,800
You hate them but you
also have to love them.

1306
01:11:48,843 --> 01:11:51,468
This is a test of your acting.
Can you do it?

1307
01:11:51,634 --> 01:11:53,218
No, he can't do it. - No way.

1308
01:11:53,384 --> 01:11:55,634
He'll fail.
- He'll fail. - He'll fail.

1309
01:11:55,800 --> 01:11:57,700
Call Salman. - Music.

1310
01:11:58,843 --> 01:12:02,384
"Mr. Cool. He's the dude."

1311
01:12:26,218 --> 01:12:28,634
"We're cool. We're dudes."

1312
01:12:28,718 --> 01:12:30,926
"We've got a carefree mood."

1313
01:12:31,051 --> 01:12:34,384
"We're known for
all the wrong reasons."

1314
01:12:35,693 --> 01:12:38,193
"We're nice, we're honest."

1315
01:12:38,218 --> 01:12:40,468
"We're one in a million."

1316
01:12:40,551 --> 01:12:44,384
"Stealing isn't our business."

1317
01:12:45,634 --> 01:12:46,800
"Why have you caught us?"

1318
01:12:46,843 --> 01:12:49,843
"Did we ask anyone.. for rent?"

1319
01:12:50,442 --> 01:12:51,609
"We've been framed."

1320
01:12:51,634 --> 01:12:54,900
"We've been arrested
just by accident."

1321
01:12:55,218 --> 01:12:59,551
"But believe us..
believe us we're innocent."

1322
01:12:59,926 --> 01:13:04,800
"Take a good look at us,
we're innocent."

1323
01:13:04,843 --> 01:13:09,051
"But believe us..
believe us we're innocent."

1324
01:13:09,634 --> 01:13:14,634
"We're honest, we're innocent."

1325
01:13:19,218 --> 01:13:23,468
"We never did anything wrong."

1326
01:13:33,634 --> 01:13:40,301
"We never did anything wrong."

1327
01:13:40,384 --> 01:13:43,134
"We never swindled anyone."

1328
01:13:43,301 --> 01:13:47,926
"You're heroes and
don't look like villains."

1329
01:13:48,051 --> 01:13:52,800
"Listen carefully..
there's no case against you here."

1330
01:13:52,843 --> 01:13:54,134
"Why did you beat us?"

1331
01:13:54,218 --> 01:13:56,843
"Why did you thrash us?
Why did you hurt us?"

1332
01:13:57,634 --> 01:14:02,134
"Your truncheons"

1333
01:14:02,468 --> 01:14:06,551
"But believe us..
believe us we're innocent."

1334
01:14:07,218 --> 01:14:12,384
"Take a good look at us,
we're innocent."

1335
01:14:17,134 --> 01:14:19,134
"He's go the moves."

1336
01:14:19,468 --> 01:14:21,551
"He's so cool."

1337
01:14:21,634 --> 01:14:24,843
"We like that."

1338
01:14:26,384 --> 01:14:28,634
"He's go the moves."

1339
01:14:29,051 --> 01:14:31,134
"He's so cool."

1340
01:14:31,468 --> 01:14:35,718
"We like that. - Come on, now!"

1341
01:14:35,843 --> 01:14:40,718
"Hey, release us
from these handcuffs."

1342
01:14:40,800 --> 01:14:45,418
"Speak respectfully with the jailor."

1343
01:14:45,551 --> 01:14:50,318
"Sir, you're the pride of India here."

1344
01:14:50,384 --> 01:14:55,134
"Hey buddy, I am your only hope here."

1345
01:14:55,218 --> 01:14:57,384
"You're our support.
You're our only kin."

1346
01:14:57,468 --> 01:14:59,301
"Don't be arrogant."

1347
01:14:59,926 --> 01:15:03,800
"We'll lose our homes.
Your guns will torment us forever."

1348
01:15:04,800 --> 01:15:08,926
"I know now.. I know you're innocent."

1349
01:15:09,634 --> 01:15:14,218
"Now I know for sure
that you're innocent."

1350
01:15:14,301 --> 01:15:18,634
"I know now.. I know you're innocent."

1351
01:15:19,051 --> 01:15:23,968
"Now this is my order
that you're innocent."

1352
01:15:26,800 --> 01:15:28,926
Mr. Director, say cut.

1353
01:15:28,968 --> 01:15:31,134
Sir, the director
fled with the artists.

1354
01:15:32,301 --> 01:15:34,926
Yes, sir. - Ran away?

1355
01:15:36,360 --> 01:15:37,443
Thank you, Mr. OP.

1356
01:15:37,468 --> 01:15:38,968
Thank you very much.
You've done us a favor.

1357
01:15:39,218 --> 01:15:41,718
I'll give you back all your tapes.

1358
01:15:41,843 --> 01:15:45,301
First give me back my family.
- What family?

1359
01:15:45,468 --> 01:15:48,843
Yes. Your men kidnapped
them in order to save you.

1360
01:15:49,384 --> 01:15:50,951
Who? - Our men?

1361
01:15:54,551 --> 01:15:55,843
Welcome. - Marcos.

1362
01:15:56,551 --> 01:16:00,551
Hi, babies. - Hello, boys.

1363
01:16:00,634 --> 01:16:01,926
Khokha.

1364
01:16:02,634 --> 01:16:05,718
Once.. in a blue moon.

1365
01:16:09,926 --> 01:16:12,551
Your family will reach home safely.

1366
01:16:12,634 --> 01:16:13,718
You go.

1367
01:16:16,218 --> 01:16:18,134
Poor babies.

1368
01:16:19,301 --> 01:16:20,551
Good shot.

1369
01:16:21,843 --> 01:16:23,634
Where are the diamonds? - Diamonds.

1370
01:16:23,926 --> 01:16:27,634
What's this new problem
of the diamonds? - Which diamonds?

1371
01:16:27,843 --> 01:16:30,051
The same diamonds you stole
from the minister's safe..

1372
01:16:30,134 --> 01:16:32,718
..before we could get them.

1373
01:16:36,551 --> 01:16:39,218
Sir, there's a confusion.

1374
01:16:39,634 --> 01:16:40,926
We committed the theft.

1375
01:16:40,968 --> 01:16:42,843
But we didn't steal any diamonds.

1376
01:16:44,468 --> 01:16:47,301
The minister said that
the diamonds were in the safe.

1377
01:16:47,452 --> 01:16:51,628
And these scoundrels
say there were no diamonds.

1378
01:16:56,134 --> 01:16:58,384
Can I say something, Mr.
Marcos? - Yes.

1379
01:16:58,468 --> 01:16:59,968
You're their boss, speak.

1380
01:17:00,134 --> 01:17:01,800
There's no driver of the bus.

1381
01:17:01,968 --> 01:17:04,968
You can all ask questions,
but let someone drive. Please.

1382
01:17:05,468 --> 01:17:06,800
The diamonds were worth millions..

1383
01:17:06,843 --> 01:17:08,468
..and we stole them
with great difficulty.

1384
01:17:08,551 --> 01:17:10,551
And you got it very easily.

1385
01:17:11,218 --> 01:17:14,718
So naturally you won't tell us easily.

1386
01:17:14,968 --> 01:17:15,734
That's true.

1387
01:17:16,128 --> 01:17:19,134
If the diamonds are worth
millions then no one will say it.

1388
01:17:20,301 --> 01:17:22,551
Marcos, the bus is heading
towards the ravines.

1389
01:17:22,634 --> 01:17:24,134
Marcos.

1390
01:17:24,218 --> 01:17:26,384
Dumbo. - Yes, boss. - Dumbo.

1391
01:17:27,218 --> 01:17:28,800
I'll tell you, quickly. - Yes.

1392
01:17:28,843 --> 01:17:32,800
Dumbo. Stop it.

1393
01:17:37,926 --> 01:17:40,718
Darling. Where are you?

1394
01:17:40,926 --> 01:17:42,926
She's getting a completely
different type of a fit today.

1395
01:17:43,468 --> 01:17:45,051
This is the third attack.

1396
01:17:45,384 --> 01:17:47,468
And what about the attack on me?

1397
01:17:47,800 --> 01:17:51,634
The criminals ran away
and you didn't even realize.

1398
01:17:51,718 --> 01:17:53,468
I realized. I realized.

1399
01:17:53,551 --> 01:17:55,384
I could've caught them as well.

1400
01:17:55,634 --> 01:17:57,384
But the director didn't say cut.

1401
01:17:57,718 --> 01:17:59,634
What could I have done? Ruin the shot.

1402
01:17:59,800 --> 01:18:02,134
What was the need to be a hero?

1403
01:18:02,134 --> 01:18:05,218
Kajal, I say let's forget the past.

1404
01:18:07,301 --> 01:18:09,301
Run. Run.

1405
01:18:11,926 --> 01:18:15,068
No. I am your daddy. Arjun's there.

1406
01:18:15,134 --> 01:18:16,301
No. No.

1407
01:18:21,800 --> 01:18:24,926
Kamini..

1408
01:18:37,718 --> 01:18:38,926
Father-in-law, you are here?

1409
01:18:39,843 --> 01:18:40,926
She's here.

1410
01:18:42,134 --> 01:18:43,843
Father-in-law, run.. Run.

1411
01:18:43,926 --> 01:18:46,718
Outside, in the water. Under water.

1412
01:18:47,301 --> 01:18:48,468
Jump.

1413
01:18:53,051 --> 01:18:53,934
Arjun.

1414
01:18:57,134 --> 01:18:58,101
Arjun.

1415
01:18:58,718 --> 01:19:01,734
Do something? - Why?

1416
01:19:01,843 --> 01:19:05,634
You've defamed me in
the entire police department..

1417
01:19:05,718 --> 01:19:08,301
..by fixing that murderer's
alliance with my daughter.

1418
01:19:09,218 --> 01:19:12,384
I say let's forget the past, Papa.

1419
01:19:12,468 --> 01:19:14,800
Forget it, now.

1420
01:19:14,926 --> 01:19:17,551
Arjun. - Arjun's dead.

1421
01:19:17,800 --> 01:19:21,418
I never waited for
the train at the station.

1422
01:19:21,468 --> 01:19:23,301
But today I am waiting for
the train lying on the tracks.

1423
01:19:23,384 --> 01:19:24,926
My wife. My children.

1424
01:19:27,718 --> 01:19:29,384
He's here.

1425
01:19:30,301 --> 01:19:32,301
Our savior is here.

1426
01:19:35,800 --> 01:19:37,926
Come on. Come.

1427
01:19:38,301 --> 01:19:40,301
Our savior is here.

1428
01:19:40,800 --> 01:19:41,926
Come.

1429
01:19:48,030 --> 01:19:49,905
Excuse me, what are you doing?

1430
01:19:50,134 --> 01:19:51,468
I am dying. Don't you see?

1431
01:19:51,551 --> 01:19:52,718
I am committing suicide.

1432
01:19:54,134 --> 01:19:55,218
What fate!

1433
01:19:55,634 --> 01:19:58,051
Our savior is committing
suicide himself.

1434
01:19:58,843 --> 01:20:00,468
Brother, you can go ahead and die.

1435
01:20:00,493 --> 01:20:02,868
But first save us. - Why you..

1436
01:20:04,634 --> 01:20:05,800
Do You see?

1437
01:20:06,718 --> 01:20:07,926
Is this world worth living in?

1438
01:20:08,051 --> 01:20:09,018
People like these..

1439
01:20:09,384 --> 01:20:10,351
Why should I stay alive?

1440
01:20:10,926 --> 01:20:12,301
Everyone wants to live.

1441
01:20:12,384 --> 01:20:14,926
But no one's asking the
dying person why he wants to die.

1442
01:20:15,134 --> 01:20:17,051
We were going to ask after
you'd have saved us, sir.

1443
01:20:17,218 --> 01:20:18,551
No, no, we'll ask first.

1444
01:20:18,634 --> 01:20:20,384
Brother, why are you trying to die?

1445
01:20:24,718 --> 01:20:27,301
My entire family was killed
by a bomb in Afghanistan.

1446
01:20:27,384 --> 01:20:30,401
Lord. - Parents, wife, young children.

1447
01:20:30,551 --> 01:20:32,218
They hurled a bomb and..

1448
01:20:32,634 --> 01:20:36,134
I have their photograph. - No, no.
We believe you. We believe you.

1449
01:20:36,301 --> 01:20:38,384
But.. we didn't kill them.

1450
01:20:38,468 --> 01:20:41,051
But you didn't save them either.
Then why do you want to stay alive?

1451
01:20:41,134 --> 01:20:43,718
And what will you do by staying alive?
Even if you survive today..

1452
01:20:43,800 --> 01:20:45,134
..tomorrow you'll
be killed by a bullet.

1453
01:20:45,218 --> 01:20:46,301
Or blown up by a bomb day after.

1454
01:20:46,384 --> 01:20:48,634
So it's better that
you die peacefully today.

1455
01:20:48,800 --> 01:20:50,468
Right, right.
- That's correct. - It's a nice deal.

1456
01:20:50,800 --> 01:20:52,634
Goodbye. - What now?

1457
01:20:52,926 --> 01:20:55,718
If it's a slow train,
we'll be minced slowly.

1458
01:20:55,926 --> 01:20:59,534
And if it's a fast train..
then we'll become mincemeat.

1459
01:21:00,843 --> 01:21:02,218
Come on. Come on.

1460
01:21:02,301 --> 01:21:04,800
No, no!

1461
01:21:04,843 --> 01:21:06,718
No. - Come on.

1462
01:21:07,218 --> 01:21:08,718
Release us. - Release us.

1463
01:21:08,800 --> 01:21:10,800
He wants to die. - No!

1464
01:21:17,277 --> 01:21:18,693
Which track are you running it on?

1465
01:21:18,718 --> 01:21:19,968
I haven't done anything.. - Stop the..

1466
01:21:20,087 --> 01:21:21,171
You saved me again.

1467
01:21:21,843 --> 01:21:24,634
You know if I come up there,
I'll ask many questions.

1468
01:21:28,926 --> 01:21:30,926
What the hell are you doing?

1469
01:21:32,134 --> 01:21:33,551
That's fate.

1470
01:21:34,134 --> 01:21:36,468
Who wants to die and who's dying.

1471
01:21:36,718 --> 01:21:39,384
Reverse. Reverse. Reverse.

1472
01:21:43,926 --> 01:21:45,134
Stop the train.

1473
01:21:45,843 --> 01:21:48,551
Stop the train.

1474
01:21:57,218 --> 01:21:58,101
Diamonds.

1475
01:21:58,551 --> 01:22:00,843
You doubt me? - Who else?

1476
01:22:01,218 --> 01:22:03,218
You took the money out of the safe.

1477
01:22:03,301 --> 01:22:05,634
I gave the bag to boss.
Right in front of you.

1478
01:22:05,843 --> 01:22:09,384
Don't raise your hand on me.

1479
01:22:10,134 --> 01:22:12,968
Thieves.
Do you think I'm like you two?

1480
01:22:13,634 --> 01:22:14,843
I am an honest man.

1481
01:22:14,926 --> 01:22:17,151
I swear on you,
I don't have the diamonds.

1482
01:22:17,384 --> 01:22:19,800
And I swear on my wife and children.

1483
01:22:19,926 --> 01:22:21,468
Then where are the diamonds?

1484
01:22:21,634 --> 01:22:24,468
Marcos doesn't have them.
You guys have them.

1485
01:22:24,551 --> 01:22:26,968
If I don't have them,
then where have the diamonds gone?

1486
01:22:27,551 --> 01:22:30,468
Can I.. say something? - Say it.

1487
01:22:30,843 --> 01:22:33,634
Please don't get angry. - Say it.

1488
01:22:34,384 --> 01:22:36,718
We swore, so you swear too.

1489
01:22:40,468 --> 01:22:43,843
Boss, I don't have
any relation with you..

1490
01:22:44,738 --> 01:22:46,538
..but you're a nice man.

1491
01:22:47,634 --> 01:22:50,468
And he's..
he's always been close to me.

1492
01:22:50,800 --> 01:22:52,843
My friend, my brother, my life.

1493
01:22:53,718 --> 01:22:58,734
I swear on you two,
I don't have the diamonds.

1494
01:22:58,843 --> 01:23:02,468
"You're a villain and not a hero."

1495
01:23:02,843 --> 01:23:06,301
"Arjun, you're a pain in the neck."

1496
01:23:06,968 --> 01:23:09,468
Arjun, you've made the case worse.

1497
01:23:09,718 --> 01:23:10,843
What is this?

1498
01:23:11,051 --> 01:23:13,384
Earlier she'd have only
one fit in a day for 10 minutes.

1499
01:23:13,468 --> 01:23:15,301
And now she gets
three-four fits a day..

1500
01:23:15,384 --> 01:23:16,843
..which lasts two-three hours.

1501
01:23:17,384 --> 01:23:19,134
You broke her sister's engagement.

1502
01:23:19,301 --> 01:23:20,551
Tarnished her father's honor.

1503
01:23:20,843 --> 01:23:22,134
Got your daughter
dropped out of school.

1504
01:23:22,218 --> 01:23:24,384
Let's forget the past, Doctor.

1505
01:23:24,468 --> 01:23:25,926
Now tell me how will she get better?

1506
01:23:25,968 --> 01:23:27,468
She won't get better now.

1507
01:23:27,718 --> 01:23:29,634
It's impossible for
her to get better now.

1508
01:23:29,718 --> 01:23:30,843
No, no, Doctor.

1509
01:23:31,051 --> 01:23:33,134
At least get her back
to her earlier condition.

1510
01:23:33,384 --> 01:23:35,468
Where she had one fit in
a day for 10 minutes. - Yes, Doctor.

1511
01:23:35,551 --> 01:23:37,384
We're used to it now.

1512
01:23:37,468 --> 01:23:39,384
Give her shock treatment.

1513
01:23:39,968 --> 01:23:43,218
Do something she
doesn't expect at all.

1514
01:23:43,551 --> 01:23:45,218
Give her happiness. Happiness.

1515
01:23:45,468 --> 01:23:47,051
You broke her sister's engagement,
didn't you?

1516
01:23:47,218 --> 01:23:48,718
Now you get her sister married.

1517
01:23:48,800 --> 01:23:51,718
But with whom? - With any cat or dog.

1518
01:23:51,905 --> 01:23:53,780
I mean with anyone.

1519
01:23:53,926 --> 01:23:57,218
Anyone. The D.I.
G's son is not too bad. Rahul.

1520
01:23:57,468 --> 01:23:58,800
He also likes Sanjana.

1521
01:23:58,843 --> 01:24:01,218
But will Sanjana agree? - Papa.

1522
01:24:01,634 --> 01:24:03,468
People who're betrayed
in love commit murders..

1523
01:24:03,551 --> 01:24:05,134
..suicide,
so marriage is not difficult.

1524
01:24:05,218 --> 01:24:07,134
We'll convince her.
You just prepare for the wedding.

1525
01:24:07,218 --> 01:24:08,284
Arjun.

1526
01:24:08,800 --> 01:24:09,743
No.

1527
01:24:11,800 --> 01:24:14,926
I won't let this happen.
- And I won't let you go.

1528
01:24:15,051 --> 01:24:16,384
Look, Yash has gone out to get food.

1529
01:24:16,468 --> 01:24:17,634
Let him come back,
then we can think of something.

1530
01:24:17,718 --> 01:24:19,926
I don't have time to think. Let me go.

1531
01:24:19,968 --> 01:24:21,718
I won't let you go.
The police are there.

1532
01:24:21,800 --> 01:24:23,218
They'll kill you.

1533
01:24:23,301 --> 01:24:25,301
What will I do without Sanjana?

1534
01:24:25,634 --> 01:24:29,134
I won't let her marry anyone else
as long as I am alive. - Raj! Raj!

1535
01:24:30,384 --> 01:24:32,843
He's gone out to get food,
wonder when he'll return.

1536
01:24:33,134 --> 01:24:35,468
And he's gone to get
shot and won't return again.

1537
01:24:35,718 --> 01:24:37,718
Raj. Raj.

1538
01:24:43,218 --> 01:24:44,800
No, no, don't cry.

1539
01:24:44,926 --> 01:24:46,234
You're looking so nice.

1540
01:24:46,384 --> 01:24:47,718
The makeup will get spoilt.

1541
01:24:47,800 --> 01:24:49,718
That's why I am crying inside.

1542
01:24:50,777 --> 01:24:53,193
Forget that deceiver.

1543
01:24:53,218 --> 01:24:55,926
In spite of whoever he
was he was still my first love.

1544
01:24:56,384 --> 01:24:59,718
I see him all the time.

1545
01:25:02,843 --> 01:25:04,384
Oh, God. - What happened?

1546
01:25:05,134 --> 01:25:07,468
Even now I can imagine
him walking up to me.

1547
01:25:07,718 --> 01:25:08,700
Yeah, right.

1548
01:25:10,384 --> 01:25:12,468
You're not imagining, it's him.

1549
01:25:14,468 --> 01:25:15,800
How dare he!

1550
01:25:16,718 --> 01:25:18,551
Mr. D.I.G. He's the boy.

1551
01:25:21,384 --> 01:25:22,551
You're getting married.

1552
01:25:23,301 --> 01:25:24,634
How else should I punish you?

1553
01:25:24,718 --> 01:25:26,843
I accept any punishment
but not this one.

1554
01:25:28,159 --> 01:25:31,062
Come with me or else..
- Or else? - Or else what will you do?

1555
01:25:31,134 --> 01:25:33,718
Or else what, son?
- Why are you silent? Say it.

1556
01:25:33,800 --> 01:25:35,134
What will you do?

1557
01:25:35,718 --> 01:25:36,843
I will shoot.

1558
01:25:38,134 --> 01:25:39,926
You will shoot. Shoot

1559
01:25:40,551 --> 01:25:42,926
How could you think
that I'd shoot at you?

1560
01:25:46,134 --> 01:25:49,468
Raj. You can't do that.

1561
01:25:49,800 --> 01:25:52,843
You know how crazy I am.

1562
01:25:54,551 --> 01:25:56,551
Don't worry. Don't worry.

1563
01:25:56,718 --> 01:25:59,384
I don't keep my gun
loaded because of someone.

1564
01:26:00,551 --> 01:26:02,551
Hey, boys, arrest him.

1565
01:26:03,800 --> 01:26:04,968
Great.

1566
01:26:06,468 --> 01:26:09,468
Papa, what happened?
- Not here, but there.

1567
01:26:09,968 --> 01:26:12,384
But my revolver is never empty.

1568
01:26:12,843 --> 01:26:16,634
If anyone tries to move,
I will kill the groom first.

1569
01:26:16,843 --> 01:26:19,134
And then the guests one by one.

1570
01:26:19,218 --> 01:26:22,218
I think you don't
know what you are doing.

1571
01:26:22,301 --> 01:26:25,468
We've done so many things
without telling anyone.

1572
01:26:25,718 --> 01:26:28,134
I didn't become a
boss by doing nothing.

1573
01:26:30,134 --> 01:26:31,118
What is this bag?

1574
01:26:31,468 --> 01:26:32,926
It was lying upstairs
so I picked it up.

1575
01:26:33,718 --> 01:26:35,926
I'll have to give
daughter-in-law some gift.

1576
01:26:36,301 --> 01:26:37,718
I have another plan.

1577
01:26:37,800 --> 01:26:39,218
Do you? - Yes. - Try it.

1578
01:26:40,718 --> 01:26:43,551
You've taken the D.I. G's son hostage.
- D.I. G?

1579
01:26:43,718 --> 01:26:45,318
Do you know what
can be the consequences?

1580
01:26:45,468 --> 01:26:47,551
You told me that they're
getting Sanjana married..

1581
01:26:47,634 --> 01:26:49,384
..to some laundryman's son.
- Yes.

1582
01:26:49,843 --> 01:26:51,634
Mr. D.I. G's surname is
'Dhobi' (Laundryman).

1583
01:26:53,051 --> 01:26:54,218
No Problem,

1584
01:26:54,301 --> 01:26:56,968
What else will you make me do,
scoundrels?

1585
01:26:58,634 --> 01:27:00,468
Father, I've switched off the lights.

1586
01:27:00,551 --> 01:27:04,218
They can't see us now.
Catch them. Catch them.

1587
01:27:05,634 --> 01:27:07,218
Sorry. - Hey! Relax.

1588
01:27:07,301 --> 01:27:09,634
Situation under control.
Calm down, relax.

1589
01:27:12,218 --> 01:27:13,284
Daddy, where is Sanjana?

1590
01:27:13,634 --> 01:27:15,926
Where is Sanjana?
- Where have they gone?

1591
01:27:15,968 --> 01:27:17,301
I think they fled.

1592
01:27:17,384 --> 01:27:20,634
No Problem, No Problem,

1593
01:27:21,384 --> 01:27:22,800
No Problem,

1594
01:27:40,634 --> 01:27:42,800
Petrol. Petrol.

1595
01:27:42,843 --> 01:27:44,134
Not on the face. Not on the face.

1596
01:27:44,218 --> 01:27:45,926
Pour it anywhere but the face.
- Not on the face.

1597
01:27:47,134 --> 01:27:48,218
Not on the face.

1598
01:27:48,843 --> 01:27:50,384
There's still time.

1599
01:27:50,551 --> 01:27:54,218
Look. Here's the minister's
murder recording. Look.

1600
01:27:54,551 --> 01:27:57,468
Take the evidence of your
innocence and give us the diamonds.

1601
01:27:57,551 --> 01:28:00,901
How many times do I tell
you we don't have the diamonds?

1602
01:28:00,926 --> 01:28:02,651
But I have an idea.

1603
01:28:03,134 --> 01:28:06,568
Give us this tape so that
we can prove ourselves innocent.

1604
01:28:06,634 --> 01:28:08,568
And then we can search
for the diamonds together.

1605
01:28:08,634 --> 01:28:10,800
We're dealing with scoundrels.

1606
01:28:11,968 --> 01:28:13,468
They won't listen like this.

1607
01:28:13,968 --> 01:28:17,301
Hey. - Dumbo, massage him properly.

1608
01:28:17,718 --> 01:28:18,843
Why me?

1609
01:28:18,926 --> 01:28:20,718
You get a lot of ideas.

1610
01:28:20,843 --> 01:28:24,634
The petrol will go to your
brain and burn all your ideas.

1611
01:28:24,718 --> 01:28:26,051
What are you staring at?

1612
01:28:26,384 --> 01:28:28,218
Look, this isn't drenched.
Pour it here.

1613
01:28:34,550 --> 01:28:35,926
We'll be fine, boss.

1614
01:28:35,968 --> 01:28:37,551
Until we have the diamonds.

1615
01:28:38,301 --> 01:28:39,800
But we don't have the diamonds. - Yes.

1616
01:28:39,843 --> 01:28:44,468
Till they think that we have
the diamonds they can't kill us.

1617
01:28:44,551 --> 01:28:47,134
Right. Right. We won't kill you.

1618
01:28:47,551 --> 01:28:48,843
We will only set you ablaze.

1619
01:28:49,551 --> 01:28:52,134
We'll set you ablaze
and she'll douse it.

1620
01:28:52,634 --> 01:28:55,926
We'll set you ablaze
again and she'll douse it.

1621
01:28:56,218 --> 01:28:57,468
Boss, I've got a suggestion.

1622
01:28:58,134 --> 01:29:00,301
Why doesn't she set
us ablaze and you douse us?

1623
01:29:00,718 --> 01:29:02,301
She'll set us ablaze
again and you douse us.

1624
01:29:02,384 --> 01:29:04,276
What difference will that make?
You won't get burnt?

1625
01:29:04,301 --> 01:29:06,051
Of course I will.

1626
01:29:06,468 --> 01:29:09,968
But it won't have that
smouldering sensation.

1627
01:29:10,800 --> 01:29:12,800
What does it mean? What does it mean?

1628
01:29:12,843 --> 01:29:15,134
Is it necessary for
everything to have a meaning?

1629
01:29:15,218 --> 01:29:17,718
But what does it mean?
- Just a minute.

1630
01:29:17,926 --> 01:29:20,134
It won't have that
smouldering sensation.

1631
01:29:20,134 --> 01:29:22,134
It won't have..

1632
01:29:22,134 --> 01:29:23,551
Boss. - What are you repeating for?

1633
01:29:23,634 --> 01:29:25,134
Set him ablaze. I'll do it.

1634
01:29:29,776 --> 01:29:32,276
Douse this fire! - Water.

1635
01:29:32,301 --> 01:29:35,484
What are you doing?
Douse this fire! Water.

1636
01:29:35,551 --> 01:29:37,551
What the hell! - I am burning!

1637
01:29:37,634 --> 01:29:40,134
I'll help you. God, I am also on fire.

1638
01:29:40,218 --> 01:29:41,268
Pour water.

1639
01:29:43,134 --> 01:29:45,134
God, I am also on fire.

1640
01:29:45,134 --> 01:29:46,218
I can't turn it on.

1641
01:29:47,968 --> 01:29:49,926
I am on fire.

1642
01:29:50,051 --> 01:29:53,843
Help! Help!

1643
01:29:55,634 --> 01:29:56,843
Come on.

1644
01:29:57,134 --> 01:29:59,843
Come after me.

1645
01:30:06,468 --> 01:30:09,468
Scoundrels, we won't spare you.

1646
01:30:12,134 --> 01:30:16,468
Hello, the one wearing the coat.
Hey, man with the cap.

1647
01:30:18,218 --> 01:30:20,051
Our boss is a don.

1648
01:30:21,468 --> 01:30:23,634
Come on. - Keep swimming.

1649
01:30:23,718 --> 01:30:24,925
Come on, swim.

1650
01:30:31,134 --> 01:30:32,634
Boss, we're safe.

1651
01:30:32,718 --> 01:30:34,134
Why are you crying if we are safe?

1652
01:30:34,384 --> 01:30:36,718
There's a hole in the boat.

1653
01:30:38,384 --> 01:30:40,134
Hey you, do you want to die?

1654
01:30:40,218 --> 01:30:41,800
What should I stay alive for, madam?

1655
01:30:41,843 --> 01:30:44,651
Couldn't you tell us that
there's a hole in the boat?

1656
01:30:44,718 --> 01:30:46,068
We could've gone to another boat.

1657
01:30:46,134 --> 01:30:47,551
He's crazy, plug the hole.

1658
01:30:47,634 --> 01:30:49,051
Plug the hole. - Yes, I am crazy.

1659
01:30:49,301 --> 01:30:51,384
My entire family was killed in Iraq,
where were you?

1660
01:30:51,800 --> 01:30:53,384
But what's our fault?

1661
01:30:53,468 --> 01:30:55,634
The entire world knows
whose mistake it is.

1662
01:30:55,718 --> 01:30:57,218
But you're clinging on to him.

1663
01:30:57,301 --> 01:30:59,218
Did you ask him why he's
killing people? Now you all die.

1664
01:30:59,301 --> 01:31:02,018
Scoundrel, we won't die yet.

1665
01:31:02,051 --> 01:31:04,634
Why you.. - Fool,
what's that heading towards us?

1666
01:31:16,094 --> 01:31:17,511
Sign on these papers.

1667
01:31:17,678 --> 01:31:19,094
What? What should I do?

1668
01:31:19,760 --> 01:31:21,986
Sign on these papers, son.

1669
01:31:22,011 --> 01:31:23,800
You didn't have to
make papers, Father.

1670
01:31:24,011 --> 01:31:26,928
Could we achieve anything
by shouting till date?

1671
01:31:27,094 --> 01:31:29,511
And also, my health is not well.

1672
01:31:29,815 --> 01:31:32,006
What was the need to
prepare the documents, father?

1673
01:31:33,760 --> 01:31:36,344
Anyway, after you I
am going to own everything.

1674
01:31:36,678 --> 01:31:38,594
The house, property.. Right, Kajal?

1675
01:31:38,760 --> 01:31:41,678
These isn't my will.

1676
01:31:42,011 --> 01:31:46,886
I am talking about
your divorce with Kajal.

1677
01:31:47,678 --> 01:31:50,261
How could you say something
I can never even imagine?

1678
01:31:51,803 --> 01:31:54,594
If you're the commissioner
then I am an inspector. Senior.

1679
01:31:55,178 --> 01:31:58,678
And nobody in this world
can make me sign against my will.

1680
01:31:58,760 --> 01:31:59,659
Sign it!

1681
01:32:03,178 --> 01:32:04,394
Sign it!

1682
01:32:07,261 --> 01:32:09,094
You don't keep a loaded gun..

1683
01:32:10,178 --> 01:32:12,094
..and consider yourself
to be a big hunter.

1684
01:32:12,178 --> 01:32:15,428
Kajal. - You can't even
hit one bird with two stones..

1685
01:32:15,511 --> 01:32:17,511
..and you try to hit
two birds with one stone.

1686
01:32:17,536 --> 01:32:20,803
Grandpa. Mummy is getting
a new kind of fit. - Yes, dear.

1687
01:32:20,886 --> 01:32:22,594
Sign it. - Kajal, Kajal.

1688
01:32:22,678 --> 01:32:23,803
What Kajal?

1689
01:32:24,011 --> 01:32:26,094
That criminal abducted
Kajal's sister..

1690
01:32:26,178 --> 01:32:28,678
..and you just watched. - I.. I.. I..

1691
01:32:28,760 --> 01:32:30,886
Sign it. - I'll do it.. I'll do it.

1692
01:32:34,428 --> 01:32:36,361
Mistake. It's burnt my mistake.

1693
01:32:37,760 --> 01:32:40,760
Arjun! No Problem,

1694
01:32:57,094 --> 01:33:00,361
Kamini. Kamini.
I say let's forget the past.

1695
01:33:01,695 --> 01:33:03,003
Past. Past.

1696
01:33:03,178 --> 01:33:05,178
You like covering up the past,
don't you?

1697
01:33:05,261 --> 01:33:06,803
No. No. - Here.

1698
01:33:14,344 --> 01:33:17,760
Grandpa, please save my father.
- Let him die.

1699
01:33:17,803 --> 01:33:20,011
He's a pain in the neck. - Grandpa.

1700
01:33:40,511 --> 01:33:43,178
Yash. These innocent people
got involved unnecessarily.

1701
01:33:44,678 --> 01:33:46,928
She's innocent.
Isn't he innocent as well?

1702
01:33:47,355 --> 01:33:48,980
He hasn't harmed anyone.

1703
01:33:49,005 --> 01:33:50,588
He just took us home once..

1704
01:33:50,803 --> 01:33:52,344
..and then lost his house and family.

1705
01:33:52,678 --> 01:33:55,886
Just think about his family's
condition without him.

1706
01:33:56,261 --> 01:33:58,803
Raj, let's make a promise.

1707
01:34:00,261 --> 01:34:01,886
If he's killed in an encounter..

1708
01:34:02,594 --> 01:34:06,011
..then we'll raise
his children. - Done.

1709
01:34:06,843 --> 01:34:09,218
And what about the wife?
- She'll get married again.

1710
01:34:09,384 --> 01:34:12,384
She's smart. - Quiet, you scoundrels.

1711
01:34:12,468 --> 01:34:14,634
Quiet. - What happened, Uncle?
- Did you hear?

1712
01:34:14,926 --> 01:34:17,301
They're saying that they'll
kill me in an encounter..

1713
01:34:17,384 --> 01:34:20,843
..and get my wife remarried
and will take care of my children.

1714
01:34:21,301 --> 01:34:24,718
Rascals. I curse you.

1715
01:34:24,800 --> 01:34:26,843
You think I'll die
and you two will survive?

1716
01:34:27,051 --> 01:34:28,218
Is it?

1717
01:34:31,468 --> 01:34:34,134
Who was it?
- Billa. Murderer. - Billa.

1718
01:34:34,384 --> 01:34:35,968
They're still after us.

1719
01:34:37,384 --> 01:34:38,843
There's someone upstairs. Come on.

1720
01:34:39,384 --> 01:34:41,926
What will we do? - What are
we going to do? - Wait, let me think.

1721
01:34:44,634 --> 01:34:46,134
Hey, you..

1722
01:34:54,468 --> 01:34:56,968
Who's there?
- Should I throw a hand grenade?

1723
01:34:58,134 --> 01:35:01,551
No, no. We've laid mines. - Mines.

1724
01:35:01,843 --> 01:35:03,968
Whoever steps on it will get blown up.

1725
01:35:04,353 --> 01:35:05,603
Sofia, careful.

1726
01:35:05,718 --> 01:35:09,134
Oh, God. This scud
missile is really amazing.

1727
01:35:09,218 --> 01:35:11,218
Should I blow up
that tank and test it?

1728
01:35:11,301 --> 01:35:15,468
No, We've sold one diamond
and bought these arms to kill Marcos.

1729
01:35:15,926 --> 01:35:17,193
You did the right thing.

1730
01:35:17,218 --> 01:35:19,301
Otherwise Marcos
wouldn't have spared us.

1731
01:35:19,384 --> 01:35:20,843
He's a dangerous man.

1732
01:35:21,218 --> 01:35:22,634
What dangerous?

1733
01:35:22,843 --> 01:35:24,218
He's a big balloon.

1734
01:35:25,301 --> 01:35:28,384
He lays us on the tracks
and the train comes after him.

1735
01:35:28,968 --> 01:35:31,134
He pours petrol on
us and gets burnt himself.

1736
01:35:31,634 --> 01:35:34,968
That's because of his four foolish
accomplices. - We are insulted.

1737
01:35:35,718 --> 01:35:38,551
And the fifth one? - She's a queen.

1738
01:35:38,926 --> 01:35:42,134
I've seen love in
her eyes for me. - Yes.

1739
01:35:42,218 --> 01:35:45,134
On the yacht, she was
making gestures at me secretly.

1740
01:35:45,634 --> 01:35:48,051
Then she's sister-in-law. - No.

1741
01:35:48,134 --> 01:35:49,718
Come on, pick up the weapons.

1742
01:35:49,926 --> 01:35:52,026
Be careful with the bazooka.

1743
01:35:52,051 --> 01:35:55,401
And listen don't forget
that we've laid the mines.

1744
01:36:09,468 --> 01:36:11,634
Boss, they left.

1745
01:36:11,800 --> 01:36:13,218
But how will we get out?

1746
01:36:15,301 --> 01:36:16,384
Marcos.

1747
01:36:18,551 --> 01:36:20,800
Run. - Follow them, come on. Move it.

1748
01:36:30,051 --> 01:36:33,051
Wow, lovely.

1749
01:36:34,051 --> 01:36:35,201
Let's go inside. Inside.

1750
01:36:50,134 --> 01:36:51,800
All arrangements done. - Yes, sir.

1751
01:36:56,134 --> 01:36:58,926
Why is there such a big reward on me?

1752
01:36:59,634 --> 01:37:02,968
Because you're the boss. - Boss.

1753
01:37:03,134 --> 01:37:05,026
This.. is a police station, Raj.

1754
01:37:05,051 --> 01:37:06,800
This.. is a police station, come on.

1755
01:37:12,843 --> 01:37:16,843
Greetings. - Wow!
What a lucky police station this is?

1756
01:37:17,218 --> 01:37:18,468
The opening's tomorrow..

1757
01:37:18,551 --> 01:37:19,926
..and the criminals
have arrived today.

1758
01:37:20,301 --> 01:37:22,218
Where are the rest? - Right here.

1759
01:37:24,134 --> 01:37:25,134
They ran away.

1760
01:37:25,218 --> 01:37:27,134
But I didn't run. But I didn't run.

1761
01:37:27,384 --> 01:37:28,551
You're tired as well.

1762
01:37:28,634 --> 01:37:30,926
Yes, I am tired. But I didn't run.

1763
01:37:30,968 --> 01:37:33,051
I didn't run.
And why should I run, sir?

1764
01:37:33,218 --> 01:37:35,134
When I haven't done anything
then why should I run?

1765
01:37:35,218 --> 01:37:36,301
I am innocent, sir.

1766
01:37:36,384 --> 01:37:37,551
We'll find out how innocent you are..

1767
01:37:37,634 --> 01:37:39,468
..as soon as we reach
the headquarters.

1768
01:37:39,718 --> 01:37:40,800
How is that, sir?

1769
01:37:40,926 --> 01:37:43,718
We've got a machine, a lie detector.

1770
01:37:44,051 --> 01:37:46,718
And it can detect lies and the truth.

1771
01:37:47,384 --> 01:37:49,218
You have such a machine? - Yes.

1772
01:37:49,301 --> 01:37:51,218
Sir, why didn't you say that earlier?

1773
01:37:51,301 --> 01:37:53,218
Sir, I kept running and running.

1774
01:37:53,301 --> 01:37:56,218
Sir, take me to that
machine right now. Come, sir.

1775
01:37:56,384 --> 01:37:57,718
This machine isn't working.

1776
01:37:58,134 --> 01:37:59,800
It's stating wrong as
right and right as wrong.

1777
01:37:59,843 --> 01:38:01,301
Repair it quickly.

1778
01:38:01,384 --> 01:38:03,926
Or else some honest man
will get beaten up by our boss.

1779
01:38:03,988 --> 01:38:04,596
Sir.

1780
01:38:08,055 --> 01:38:10,139
So, this is the machine.
- Sit down.

1781
01:38:22,384 --> 01:38:24,384
Sir, this..
- No disturbance during interrogation.

1782
01:38:24,551 --> 01:38:26,301
But, sir, this.. - Shut up.

1783
01:38:26,551 --> 01:38:28,843
Or else I'll make you sit here.
- Sit down, sit down.

1784
01:38:28,926 --> 01:38:30,301
Sir is getting disturbed. Sit down.

1785
01:38:39,384 --> 01:38:40,409
Hello, hello.

1786
01:38:40,926 --> 01:38:43,634
What is your name? - Zandu Lal.

1787
01:38:43,686 --> 01:38:45,768
Wrong. Wrong. Wrong.

1788
01:38:47,634 --> 01:38:50,718
Who is the boss?
- Boss, I.. - Right, right, right.

1789
01:38:51,301 --> 01:38:53,551
Good. And how long have
you been running this gang?

1790
01:38:53,843 --> 01:38:54,597
Gang?

1791
01:38:57,026 --> 01:38:58,276
I run a bank.

1792
01:38:58,301 --> 01:38:59,968
Wrong. Wrong.

1793
01:39:02,468 --> 01:39:05,218
Are you a man or a woman?

1794
01:39:05,634 --> 01:39:06,472
I..

1795
01:39:10,301 --> 01:39:12,843
I am a woman.
- Right. Right. Right.

1796
01:39:15,218 --> 01:39:16,718
I had my doubt.

1797
01:39:16,926 --> 01:39:18,800
But your machine is working properly.

1798
01:39:19,926 --> 01:39:23,218
You're being tested
and not the machine.

1799
01:39:30,301 --> 01:39:33,800
How many women are you having
an affair with other than your wife?

1800
01:39:34,800 --> 01:39:36,301
Other than my wife..

1801
01:39:37,634 --> 01:39:41,468
Other than my wife I
have an affair with all women.

1802
01:39:41,551 --> 01:39:43,468
Right. Right.

1803
01:39:48,051 --> 01:39:50,634
That means sorrow in the
house and merriment outside.

1804
01:39:51,551 --> 01:39:54,051
What is this, sir? - Sugarcane.

1805
01:39:54,134 --> 01:39:55,843
Silent assassin. - Silent assassin.

1806
01:39:55,968 --> 01:39:58,218
It leaves no mark behind
but causes a lot of pain.

1807
01:40:02,051 --> 01:40:03,634
If you..

1808
01:40:07,301 --> 01:40:09,718
Hello. Hello, Kajal darling.

1809
01:40:10,551 --> 01:40:11,159
What?

1810
01:40:11,968 --> 01:40:13,034
Tuktuk is missing.

1811
01:40:13,800 --> 01:40:14,643
It's been two hours.

1812
01:40:15,134 --> 01:40:16,534
She's nowhere to be found.

1813
01:40:17,301 --> 01:40:20,026
Kajal.. Kajal, don't worry.

1814
01:40:26,134 --> 01:40:30,384
Why are you laughing?
- An underworld boss..

1815
01:40:31,968 --> 01:40:34,051
..who murdered the minister..

1816
01:40:34,301 --> 01:40:37,134
..robbed a bank,
you think you can beat him up..

1817
01:40:37,134 --> 01:40:38,926
..on grounds of right and wrong.

1818
01:40:39,218 --> 01:40:42,134
And your children
can roam around freely.

1819
01:40:42,227 --> 01:40:43,311
What do you mean?

1820
01:40:44,051 --> 01:40:49,568
I mean.. my children
have kidnapped your child.

1821
01:40:49,718 --> 01:40:51,468
Right.

1822
01:40:52,926 --> 01:40:57,026
Look, boss.
I say let's forget the past. - I see.

1823
01:40:57,134 --> 01:40:58,634
I just say that.

1824
01:40:59,634 --> 01:41:01,134
Don't harm my child, please.

1825
01:41:01,218 --> 01:41:03,134
Your child will be absolutely safe.

1826
01:41:03,301 --> 01:41:05,843
You've released me
and also given me a car.

1827
01:41:06,134 --> 01:41:07,926
I will call my gang members..

1828
01:41:07,968 --> 01:41:10,134
..and inform them to
take your child back home.

1829
01:41:11,301 --> 01:41:13,926
This boss is just..
- Why did you disconnect it.

1830
01:41:14,301 --> 01:41:15,843
He'll be safe in the police station.

1831
01:41:16,551 --> 01:41:19,468
I told them.
- But, sir, you didn't say anything.

1832
01:41:19,551 --> 01:41:22,318
I am the boss, I talk in codes.

1833
01:41:22,384 --> 01:41:26,301
"I love my heart.."

1834
01:41:26,384 --> 01:41:27,551
Hello, Kajal.

1835
01:41:27,800 --> 01:41:29,218
Don't worry, Kajal.

1836
01:41:29,384 --> 01:41:30,926
Tuktuk will come home soon.

1837
01:41:31,468 --> 01:41:33,318
What? She's at home.

1838
01:41:33,926 --> 01:41:36,384
She's at home. - Really? - Yes, Naidu.

1839
01:41:36,718 --> 01:41:37,800
Kaja, I..

1840
01:41:39,051 --> 01:41:41,318
Zandu Lal.

1841
01:41:41,384 --> 01:41:42,843
You fooled me?

1842
01:41:43,468 --> 01:41:45,718
Hey, I'll not spare him!

1843
01:41:46,218 --> 01:41:47,843
Move aside.

1844
01:41:57,843 --> 01:42:00,551
Papa. Papa, are you fine?

1845
01:42:01,218 --> 01:42:02,800
Why are you yelling at me?

1846
01:42:02,843 --> 01:42:04,050
You should look where you're going.

1847
01:42:04,134 --> 01:42:05,384
You should look where
you were going, sir.

1848
01:42:05,468 --> 01:42:06,800
It's your mistake. Yes, sir.

1849
01:42:06,843 --> 01:42:09,800
Let's forget the past,
call the ambulance, Naidu.

1850
01:42:09,843 --> 01:42:11,134
Ambulance.

1851
01:42:18,718 --> 01:42:21,218
Raj. Raj. Raj.

1852
01:42:23,968 --> 01:42:24,834
Sanjana.

1853
01:42:29,718 --> 01:42:30,843
Boss.

1854
01:42:32,634 --> 01:42:33,718
Tell me something.

1855
01:42:34,468 --> 01:42:37,384
Is your incoming free in your mobile?

1856
01:42:37,718 --> 01:42:39,468
Yes. - It is, isn't it?

1857
01:42:39,634 --> 01:42:41,384
Then why did you disconnect my call?

1858
01:42:41,926 --> 01:42:43,234
I would've been charged for the call.

1859
01:42:43,384 --> 01:42:45,134
Why did you disconnect my call?
- Uncle, don't hit Raj..

1860
01:42:45,159 --> 01:42:47,867
Quiet. I will slap you. Quiet.

1861
01:42:48,843 --> 01:42:51,926
Scoundrels. - Boss.
- You handed the diamond to me..

1862
01:42:51,951 --> 01:42:53,201
Don't hit us, boss.

1863
01:42:53,551 --> 01:42:56,134
You didn't think
what would happen to me.

1864
01:42:58,551 --> 01:43:00,634
"No problem."

1865
01:43:02,384 --> 01:43:06,718
"No problem."

1866
01:43:06,800 --> 01:43:10,134
What is this?
- It's a diamond. Diamond.

1867
01:43:10,218 --> 01:43:11,968
I can see that, fool.

1868
01:43:12,384 --> 01:43:13,718
But what are you doing with it?

1869
01:43:13,800 --> 01:43:15,134
I had them.

1870
01:43:15,468 --> 01:43:17,218
Didn't I tell you the other day?

1871
01:43:17,777 --> 01:43:20,193
That's how we brought
the fake weapons.

1872
01:43:20,218 --> 01:43:22,301
And what about when you swore on us?

1873
01:43:22,634 --> 01:43:24,384
Are you two dead?

1874
01:43:24,800 --> 01:43:27,843
Boss, please release me. I
want to say something as well, please.

1875
01:43:27,926 --> 01:43:30,218
Release him. - Release me, please.

1876
01:43:30,718 --> 01:43:31,926
Hey!

1877
01:43:32,843 --> 01:43:35,634
Boss, the sugarcane. - No.

1878
01:43:35,843 --> 01:43:37,134
Boss, no. - Boss, me too.

1879
01:43:37,218 --> 01:43:38,926
How many pieces should
I break one sugarcane into?

1880
01:43:39,134 --> 01:43:40,634
Daughter-in-law, you can't hit me.

1881
01:43:40,718 --> 01:43:43,568
I am your brother-in-law.
- You're her brother-in-law.

1882
01:43:43,718 --> 01:43:46,718
What if she had suffered
burns the other day? - Answer him.

1883
01:43:47,134 --> 01:43:48,218
We've got the diamonds.

1884
01:43:48,384 --> 01:43:49,551
We could've gotten
plastic surgery done.

1885
01:43:49,634 --> 01:43:50,843
What if your father-in-law
had lost his arms and legs..

1886
01:43:50,926 --> 01:43:52,134
..because of the train?

1887
01:43:52,134 --> 01:43:53,634
Boss, we have the diamonds.

1888
01:43:53,843 --> 01:43:55,051
We could've gotten new ones.

1889
01:43:56,800 --> 01:43:58,051
How many more diamonds do you have?

1890
01:43:58,134 --> 01:44:00,218
That's all that I have. - He's lying.

1891
01:44:00,301 --> 01:44:01,926
He's a liar. - Boss.

1892
01:44:02,551 --> 01:44:04,218
Let's take his clothes
off and search him.

1893
01:44:04,384 --> 01:44:05,634
No, no, no,
not in front of daughter-in-law.

1894
01:44:05,718 --> 01:44:07,926
Daughter-in-law, turn around.
Turn around.

1895
01:44:08,301 --> 01:44:10,468
Let's take his clothes off.
- Boss. Boss.

1896
01:44:10,551 --> 01:44:13,134
I will strip him. - No, boss.

1897
01:44:13,218 --> 01:44:16,218
Raj, what are you doing!
Raj, leave me.

1898
01:44:23,634 --> 01:44:26,551
With these diamonds I
can open up hundreds of banks.

1899
01:44:26,800 --> 01:44:29,926
I can bribe the judge,
police and the minister.

1900
01:44:30,301 --> 01:44:31,800
A few diamonds will be enough.

1901
01:44:31,926 --> 01:44:33,718
Only one diamond will be enough, Boss.

1902
01:44:35,384 --> 01:44:37,134
I've done all the calculations.

1903
01:44:37,800 --> 01:44:39,551
Come here, let me explain to you.
Come here.

1904
01:44:40,134 --> 01:44:43,718
Boss, it's not more valuable than
my love and your wife and children.

1905
01:44:44,026 --> 01:44:45,526
You want to go back to your village,
don't you? - Yes.

1906
01:44:45,551 --> 01:44:47,218
Fine, then let's give them to Marcos..

1907
01:44:47,301 --> 01:44:49,218
..and take the evidence of
our innocence. - Of course, of course.

1908
01:44:49,301 --> 01:44:51,718
It's better to bribe everyone, boss.

1909
01:44:52,026 --> 01:44:53,359
Otherwise he'll take the diamonds..

1910
01:44:53,384 --> 01:44:55,468
..kill everyone and won't
even handover the evidence.

1911
01:44:55,551 --> 01:44:58,218
Be quiet. - Shut up. - Keep
your mouth shut. - Listen to me, boss

1912
01:44:58,301 --> 01:45:02,968
Boss. Boss.
Listen to me. Be quiet. - Be quiet.

1913
01:45:05,301 --> 01:45:06,634
Yash was right.

1914
01:45:06,800 --> 01:45:08,134
We can't trust Marcos.

1915
01:45:08,718 --> 01:45:11,384
Then what should we do?
We can't approach the police.

1916
01:45:11,551 --> 01:45:12,926
They'll shoot us at sight.

1917
01:45:13,134 --> 01:45:14,800
We can get the police's help.

1918
01:45:15,468 --> 01:45:16,551
There's one way.

1919
01:45:16,634 --> 01:45:17,800
Do you want anything else, dear?

1920
01:45:17,843 --> 01:45:19,551
Mother never buys me balloons.

1921
01:45:19,968 --> 01:45:21,551
Uncle will buy it for you.

1922
01:45:21,800 --> 01:45:24,026
Why uncle? - Buy a little extra.

1923
01:45:24,134 --> 01:45:26,926
As a child,
you would argue with daddy..

1924
01:45:26,968 --> 01:45:29,134
..to fulfil every small wish of mine.

1925
01:45:29,384 --> 01:45:31,384
And today when it's
the question of my life..

1926
01:45:31,718 --> 01:45:33,301
..can't you convince daddy?

1927
01:45:33,384 --> 01:45:36,800
Here's your candy.
- And here's your balloon.

1928
01:45:37,443 --> 01:45:38,693
If we can impress the child..

1929
01:45:38,718 --> 01:45:40,218
..the mother will be
automatically impressed.

1930
01:45:44,384 --> 01:45:46,718
Sister Sanjana. Sister Sanjana.

1931
01:45:50,301 --> 01:45:51,634
Tuktuk.

1932
01:45:52,468 --> 01:45:53,926
Save me! - What did you do?

1933
01:45:54,051 --> 01:45:55,634
ou asked me to buy extra balloons.

1934
01:45:55,718 --> 01:45:57,134
But so many that the child flew away!

1935
01:45:58,218 --> 01:46:00,926
Mummy, save me. - God.

1936
01:46:00,968 --> 01:46:03,551
Someone save me.

1937
01:46:04,718 --> 01:46:06,843
"No problem."

1938
01:46:08,551 --> 01:46:10,218
Mummy. Mummy, save.

1939
01:46:11,468 --> 01:46:13,134
"No problem."

1940
01:46:13,926 --> 01:46:15,800
Give me.. - Mummy.

1941
01:46:15,843 --> 01:46:18,384
You're trying to kill my child.

1942
01:46:18,468 --> 01:46:20,800
I am saving her, I'm not killing her.
- Okay. - Blue.

1943
01:46:21,800 --> 01:46:22,926
Yellow.

1944
01:46:24,468 --> 01:46:25,634
Red. Red.

1945
01:46:29,968 --> 01:46:32,800
Your aim is good.
- I just realized that.

1946
01:46:34,468 --> 01:46:36,134
Mummy. Mummy.

1947
01:46:38,468 --> 01:46:39,634
Thank God.

1948
01:46:39,718 --> 01:46:41,218
You know how scared mother was.

1949
01:46:41,468 --> 01:46:42,843
Who gave you the balloons?

1950
01:46:47,551 --> 01:46:49,301
She was playing with us?

1951
01:46:49,718 --> 01:46:50,926
Who gave you the balloons?

1952
01:46:50,968 --> 01:46:52,551
Tell me,
dear, who gave you the balloons?

1953
01:46:52,968 --> 01:46:54,843
I think the child can't
speak because of the shock. - Yes.

1954
01:46:54,968 --> 01:46:57,551
I think it's not right
to question her right now.

1955
01:46:58,134 --> 01:47:00,468
Thank you, Raj.
If it hadn't been for you..

1956
01:47:00,843 --> 01:47:02,843
..then I wonder where my
child would've been flying today.

1957
01:47:04,384 --> 01:47:08,026
You two saved my child that's
why I'm ready to forget the past.

1958
01:47:08,218 --> 01:47:10,501
But who knocked daddy down?

1959
01:47:10,551 --> 01:47:11,634
Some enemy.

1960
01:47:11,926 --> 01:47:13,800
We haven't found that car driver yet.

1961
01:47:13,843 --> 01:47:16,051
But your brother-in-law and the
police are still searching for them.

1962
01:47:16,218 --> 01:47:18,468
You know,
Sanju, they tried to kill him..

1963
01:47:18,551 --> 01:47:20,051
Isn't it enough that he survived?

1964
01:47:20,134 --> 01:47:22,301
He's more shocked than hurt,
that's all.

1965
01:47:23,218 --> 01:47:24,800
Daddy wants to say something.

1966
01:47:27,051 --> 01:47:28,384
But he can't speak.

1967
01:47:28,718 --> 01:47:29,600
Then let him write it.

1968
01:47:30,468 --> 01:47:32,801
He isn't dying that we'll
make him write his will.

1969
01:47:33,800 --> 01:47:36,134
Sister, why is he pointing
towards brother-in-law?

1970
01:47:36,134 --> 01:47:38,468
He's asking me to help these two.

1971
01:47:38,634 --> 01:47:40,051
Oh, he'll help us.

1972
01:47:40,843 --> 01:47:44,634
Sister, give him a strong
dose of 500 cc and let him rest.

1973
01:47:44,718 --> 01:47:45,800
Yes, sir.

1974
01:47:48,926 --> 01:47:51,843
Daddy. Daddy, please cooperate.
Daddy, take the injection.

1975
01:47:54,218 --> 01:47:55,284
Now here's my plan.

1976
01:47:57,134 --> 01:47:58,718
There's a transmitter in this pen.

1977
01:47:59,843 --> 01:48:03,026
This time I will kill
three birds with one stone.

1978
01:48:03,301 --> 01:48:04,718
You won't have to give the diamonds.

1979
01:48:04,926 --> 01:48:07,218
I will get the evidence
of your innocence from Marcos..

1980
01:48:07,301 --> 01:48:08,926
..and then arrest him

1981
01:48:12,218 --> 01:48:17,134
Mike testing. One, two, three.
Inspector, are you ready?

1982
01:48:17,384 --> 01:48:19,384
Yes. Yes.
Don't worry. Don't worry, boys.

1983
01:48:19,468 --> 01:48:20,926
'Operation three birds' is ready.

1984
01:48:25,218 --> 01:48:26,718
Calm down. Calm down.

1985
01:48:27,384 --> 01:48:29,134
Welcome, babies.

1986
01:48:34,384 --> 01:48:35,251
Just you two?

1987
01:48:35,926 --> 01:48:37,843
Where is the third one? The tall one?

1988
01:48:40,134 --> 01:48:43,051
I am asking because he's dangerous.
Something could be fishy.

1989
01:48:43,134 --> 01:48:45,218
No, no, this isn't any plan.
- Diamonds.

1990
01:48:46,565 --> 01:48:47,718
Evidence.

1991
01:48:48,301 --> 01:48:49,718
Yes, the evidence.

1992
01:48:49,843 --> 01:48:53,134
We need evidence to prove
that you murdered the minister.

1993
01:48:53,218 --> 01:48:55,568
Come on, let's go.
Come on. Everybody down.

1994
01:48:56,800 --> 01:48:58,800
Sir, sir. The dog's going that way.

1995
01:48:58,843 --> 01:49:00,301
Am I the officer or is the dog?

1996
01:49:00,384 --> 01:49:02,134
Sir, you are. - Then follow me.

1997
01:49:06,468 --> 01:49:07,634
That's fine.

1998
01:49:10,926 --> 01:49:12,468
Thank you very much.

1999
01:49:13,301 --> 01:49:14,168
Wait.

2000
01:49:15,134 --> 01:49:16,118
Where are the rest of the diamonds?

2001
01:49:16,718 --> 01:49:18,826
Rest of them? What? - Diamonds.

2002
01:49:19,843 --> 01:49:21,634
That's all. - They're not.

2003
01:49:22,468 --> 01:49:24,051
This is just half. - Cut.

2004
01:49:25,718 --> 01:49:26,843
We're trapped.

2005
01:49:27,134 --> 01:49:28,926
We're trapped.

2006
01:49:29,634 --> 01:49:31,634
Don't worry, don't worry, I am coming.
We're almost there.

2007
01:49:35,301 --> 01:49:36,384
Hello, hello.

2008
01:49:36,634 --> 01:49:38,468
There's a microphone.

2009
01:49:40,634 --> 01:49:41,800
Sir, there's no one here, sir.

2010
01:49:44,718 --> 01:49:48,468
Naidu, look they're so stupid.

2011
01:49:48,551 --> 01:49:49,718
They went inside the wrong building.

2012
01:49:49,800 --> 01:49:51,218
We're in the wrong building, sir.

2013
01:49:51,301 --> 01:49:53,301
We should've followed
the dog and not you.

2014
01:49:53,384 --> 01:49:55,551
O God! Where have
you brought us, Sanju?

2015
01:49:55,634 --> 01:49:56,968
Is this a place to meet someone?

2016
01:49:57,134 --> 01:49:58,384
I should've never listened to..

2017
01:50:00,134 --> 01:50:01,843
Daughter-in-law, you?
- To hell with daughter-in-law.

2018
01:50:01,926 --> 01:50:03,051
It's all your fault.

2019
01:50:03,134 --> 01:50:05,218
Raj and uncle haven't returned
after meeting Marcos yet.

2020
01:50:05,301 --> 01:50:08,468
Arjun hasn't returned either.
- I see, Arjun went along as well.

2021
01:50:08,800 --> 01:50:10,218
If it didn't concern you, Sanju..

2022
01:50:10,362 --> 01:50:12,134
..then I wouldn't have sent
him on this dangerous mission.

2023
01:50:12,134 --> 01:50:14,800
Don't worry,
they'll be absolutely fine, okay.

2024
01:50:15,468 --> 01:50:17,134
Why haven't they called yet?

2025
01:50:20,301 --> 01:50:23,718
Hello. - You rascal,
scoundrel, cheater.

2026
01:50:23,843 --> 01:50:26,800
It's them. - Speaker. Speaker.

2027
01:50:27,926 --> 01:50:30,134
You're bound to get
stuck if you take only half.

2028
01:50:30,134 --> 01:50:32,068
Couldn't you tell us
that we're taking only half?

2029
01:50:32,134 --> 01:50:33,551
You gagged my mouth.

2030
01:50:33,634 --> 01:50:35,843
You didn't let me speak.
- Tell me something..

2031
01:50:35,926 --> 01:50:37,800
..where did you hide
the rest of the diamonds?

2032
01:50:38,134 --> 01:50:39,926
Daughter-in-law and
sister are right here.

2033
01:50:40,384 --> 01:50:41,800
Let it stay hidden.

2034
01:50:42,134 --> 01:50:43,218
Just do as I say.

2035
01:50:43,384 --> 01:50:46,700
Bring the diamonds here or
else they won't spare me and boss.

2036
01:50:48,196 --> 01:50:49,780
Did they kill Arjun?

2037
01:50:50,134 --> 01:50:51,634
He got us into this.

2038
01:50:51,843 --> 01:50:53,843
He sent us ahead and he
went inside the other building.

2039
01:50:54,051 --> 01:50:55,384
He hasn't got here.

2040
01:50:55,634 --> 01:50:58,301
He must be hiding
somewhere out of shame.

2041
01:51:01,634 --> 01:51:03,362
The coward. Sister! - What?

2042
01:51:03,551 --> 01:51:04,634
Sister! - What happened?

2043
01:51:04,718 --> 01:51:06,718
Please stay fine. - I am fine.

2044
01:51:07,134 --> 01:51:08,551
Stay fine. Stay fine.

2045
01:51:08,926 --> 01:51:10,634
Hello. - Yes, go ahead.

2046
01:51:10,718 --> 01:51:11,843
Hello, Yash.

2047
01:51:11,926 --> 01:51:13,551
What's wrong with your voice, boss?

2048
01:51:13,800 --> 01:51:18,718
Not boss, consider that
it's your father speaking.

2049
01:51:19,343 --> 01:51:20,884
I am in trouble, son.

2050
01:51:20,926 --> 01:51:23,551
These people thrashed
your father badly.

2051
01:51:25,301 --> 01:51:27,800
For the first time
someone called me son.

2052
01:51:29,218 --> 01:51:31,468
Is it okay if I call you papa?

2053
01:51:31,634 --> 01:51:34,051
Do you speak from your heart, son?
- No, Papa.

2054
01:51:34,218 --> 01:51:36,551
I am speaking from my
mouth but I really mean it.

2055
01:51:37,051 --> 01:51:39,926
I suggest you bring
the diamonds quickly.

2056
01:51:40,718 --> 01:51:42,968
Your papa has to go back
to his village, isn't it?

2057
01:51:43,218 --> 01:51:44,968
Come on.
- I am coming right away, Papa.

2058
01:51:45,134 --> 01:51:46,384
Right away.

2059
01:52:29,551 --> 01:52:30,318
Papa.

2060
01:52:34,290 --> 01:52:36,790
Idiot! What are you doing?

2061
01:52:37,718 --> 01:52:39,384
What did I do? - What did you do?

2062
01:52:39,468 --> 01:52:40,718
You dropped so many
things on my head..

2063
01:52:40,800 --> 01:52:41,926
..and now you're asking what you did.

2064
01:52:42,301 --> 01:52:43,718
You banged up my head. - Shut up!

2065
01:52:44,800 --> 01:52:47,668
It's a chain and not a thread.
It's a chain.

2066
01:52:48,218 --> 01:52:50,134
Tell me where the key is.

2067
01:52:50,301 --> 01:52:52,551
With Sofia. - What? - With Sofia.

2068
01:52:52,634 --> 01:52:53,500
Sofia?

2069
01:52:57,718 --> 01:53:00,134
Hey! Hey! - What are you doing?
- What are you doing?

2070
01:53:00,218 --> 01:53:01,843
Cutting the chain!
It can be cut with the axe.

2071
01:53:03,384 --> 01:53:05,843
Are you doing it for
the first time? - Yes.

2072
01:53:05,926 --> 01:53:08,301
Son, get some practice first.

2073
01:53:14,134 --> 01:53:15,634
Hit it, hit it.

2074
01:53:20,384 --> 01:53:21,551
Let it be, son.

2075
01:53:21,634 --> 01:53:23,384
It's better to remain tied up.

2076
01:53:23,843 --> 01:53:26,218
Your father won't
look nice without hands.

2077
01:53:26,301 --> 01:53:29,026
Papa, let me practice some more.

2078
01:53:29,051 --> 01:53:31,468
No, son.

2079
01:53:45,634 --> 01:53:46,800
Marcos!

2080
01:53:48,718 --> 01:53:50,468
See what happened to her? Come on.

2081
01:53:51,718 --> 01:53:53,634
Where are you going?
- Where are you going?

2082
01:53:53,718 --> 01:53:54,926
I am coming back, Papa.

2083
01:53:55,051 --> 01:53:56,634
I'll just get the key and come back.

2084
01:53:56,718 --> 01:53:59,301
And papa?
- He's going to get the key.

2085
